1
00:00:18,053 --> 00:00:21,613
The first short drama competition
show in Korea, Director's Arena.

2
00:00:21,613 --> 00:00:23,943
The long-awaited final round has begun.

3
00:00:23,943 --> 00:00:25,183
[Top 3 Reward]

4
00:00:25,183 --> 00:00:26,553
[1st place: 100 million won /
2nd place: 50 million won]

5
00:00:26,553 --> 00:00:29,353
[3rd place: A compact cinema
camera set for pro filmmakers]

6
00:00:29,353 --> 00:00:34,223
The final round will judge Episodes 3 to 5.

7
00:00:34,223 --> 00:00:39,063
The stop count from one episode
will roll over to the next.

8
00:00:39,063 --> 00:00:45,083
If you get over 34 stops in total,
which is over 60% of the maximum,

9
00:00:45,083 --> 00:00:48,193
the next episode will not play.

10
00:00:48,193 --> 00:00:49,363
You've got to be kidding me.

11
00:00:49,363 --> 00:00:52,973
We're the final seven. They still get to stop?

12
00:00:52,973 --> 00:00:55,373
She's here to win with "Snakes and Ladders."

13
00:00:55,373 --> 00:00:58,333
Director Han Soo Ji, please come up on stage.

14
00:00:58,333 --> 00:01:01,763
[AI-generated footage]

15
00:01:01,763 --> 00:01:03,423
Wow.

16
00:01:03,423 --> 00:01:05,983
So impressive. How did she do it?

17
00:01:05,983 --> 00:01:09,133
Wow, I'm so glad we got to watch this.

18
00:01:09,133 --> 00:01:11,123
It's totally different from Episode 1.

19
00:01:11,123 --> 00:01:13,513
The real beginning was Episode 3.

20
00:01:13,513 --> 00:01:15,433
[However]

21
00:01:15,433 --> 00:01:18,533
Will the next episode play?

22
00:01:18,533 --> 00:01:19,993
Please, please.

23
00:01:19,993 --> 00:01:21,333
Is it not going to play?

24
00:01:21,333 --> 00:01:23,783
[Heightened sense of anxiety]

25
00:01:24,483 --> 00:01:27,073
[Will he be eliminated?]

26
00:01:27,073 --> 00:01:28,623
Something went wrong.

27
00:01:28,623 --> 00:01:30,443
It was very shocking to me.

28
00:01:30,443 --> 00:01:33,513
Short drama competition show, Director's Arena.

29
00:01:33,513 --> 00:01:35,963
Who will be the final winner?

30
00:01:35,963 --> 00:01:38,263
Let's meet the next director.

31
00:01:38,263 --> 00:01:39,513
[The Top 7 are very nervous]

32
00:01:39,513 --> 00:01:44,583
All the short dramas they directed became No. 1,

33
00:01:44,583 --> 00:01:49,873
but they haven't been in first place
on Directors' Arena.

34
00:01:49,873 --> 00:01:53,593
No. 1 short-drama director, Park So Rang,
please come forward.

35
00:01:53,593 --> 00:01:55,263
[Already excited]

36
00:01:55,823 --> 00:01:57,903
Gosh, welcome.

37
00:01:57,903 --> 00:02:00,093
Director Park So Rang.

38
00:02:01,083 --> 00:02:03,463
[1:1 death match round]

39
00:02:04,523 --> 00:02:07,883
[She received two stops from the Five Stars]

40
00:02:08,693 --> 00:02:12,053
[She was eliminated in Round 3
and suffered a reversal]

41
00:02:12,053 --> 00:02:15,953
I got a message from Kyu Jong
on the morning before taping.

42
00:02:15,953 --> 00:02:19,973
He was rooting for me since it was the taping day.

43
00:02:19,973 --> 00:02:23,123
But I got eliminated. I was like,
"How do I tell him?"

44
00:02:23,123 --> 00:02:25,223
It was terrible.

45
00:02:25,223 --> 00:02:28,263
[She dramatically made a return]

46
00:02:28,263 --> 00:02:30,103
Director Park So Rang.

47
00:02:30,103 --> 00:02:32,613
You didn't look so happy the last time I saw you.

48
00:02:32,613 --> 00:02:36,013
It's nice to see you come back
with a bright smile.

49
00:02:36,723 --> 00:02:39,123
[Good luck with the final]

50
00:02:39,123 --> 00:02:42,173
Before Episode 3 starts,

51
00:02:42,173 --> 00:02:44,993
please tell us the plot of Episodes 1 and 2.

52
00:02:44,993 --> 00:02:46,933
In Episodes 1 and 2,

53
00:02:46,933 --> 00:02:51,743
Ye Na learns that her fiancé was
cheating on the wedding day.

54
00:02:51,743 --> 00:02:55,103
She ends up running away from her wedding.

55
00:02:55,103 --> 00:02:58,483
This marriage is annulled.

56
00:02:59,193 --> 00:03:01,933
The first two episodes were all
about being provocative.

57
00:03:01,933 --> 00:03:05,443
But the latter half is more about

58
00:03:05,443 --> 00:03:08,333
the romance between the two leads.

59
00:03:08,333 --> 00:03:11,113
I hope you'll look forward to it.

60
00:03:11,113 --> 00:03:16,413
Sounds good. I'm curious how many
episodes we'll be seeing today.

61
00:03:16,413 --> 00:03:19,693
We'll start the judging now.

62
00:03:19,693 --> 00:03:21,653
Play the video.

63
00:03:22,503 --> 00:03:24,353
[Will she get to play all the way
through Episode 5?]

64
00:03:24,353 --> 00:03:26,323
The directors who revived...

65
00:03:26,323 --> 00:03:29,163
It's fun to watch them back-to-back.

66
00:03:30,993 --> 00:03:33,173
To be honest, I'm scared.

67
00:03:33,173 --> 00:03:35,753
It took so much for me to get into the Top 7.

68
00:03:35,753 --> 00:03:39,743
It'll be so upsetting if I don't get
to show all five episodes.

69
00:03:39,743 --> 00:03:41,833
I feel so distressed.

70
00:03:41,833 --> 00:03:45,103
[Is This Marriage Valid?]

71
00:03:45,103 --> 00:03:48,923
This marriage is annulled.

72
00:03:49,713 --> 00:03:51,193
Shit.

73
00:03:53,023 --> 00:03:54,723
She's leaving.

74
00:03:54,723 --> 00:03:55,863
That bitch!

75
00:03:55,863 --> 00:03:58,103
What are you doing? Stop her!

76
00:04:03,423 --> 00:04:05,593
- No one told you to go on a blind date.
- There he is.

77
00:04:05,593 --> 00:04:07,893
I'm telling you to just show up.

78
00:04:07,893 --> 00:04:11,083
I heard women are lining up to see you.

79
00:04:14,163 --> 00:04:16,403
[It's showtime once again]

80
00:04:16,403 --> 00:04:18,053
- Does he know her?
- Lee Ye Na?

81
00:04:18,053 --> 00:04:19,323
Huh?

82
00:04:26,523 --> 00:04:27,883
Lee Ye Na?

83
00:04:27,883 --> 00:04:29,703
What? Do they know each other?

84
00:04:33,443 --> 00:04:35,563
Hyung, let's push it back a bit.

85
00:04:35,563 --> 00:04:36,903
What?

86
00:04:38,873 --> 00:04:40,693
It's getting good starting Episode 3.

87
00:04:41,363 --> 00:04:43,263
[Absorbed]

88
00:04:55,253 --> 00:04:57,353
- Who-
- Hush!

89
00:04:57,353 --> 00:04:58,343
Ji Han?

90
00:04:58,343 --> 00:05:01,083
Why would you run away from your wedding?

91
00:05:01,083 --> 00:05:03,793
- Pardon?
- Do you have a secret lover or something?

92
00:05:03,793 --> 00:05:07,593
Or are you determined to ruin someone again?

93
00:05:07,593 --> 00:05:09,073
What do you mean...

94
00:05:09,073 --> 00:05:12,473
Forget it. Thank you for your help.

95
00:05:13,343 --> 00:05:15,143
Will you be wearing that?

96
00:05:16,083 --> 00:05:19,433
So, you want me to help you or not?

97
00:05:19,433 --> 00:05:20,843
You want me to help you or not?

98
00:05:20,843 --> 00:05:22,373
[As the two leads meet]

99
00:05:22,373 --> 00:05:24,853
[Episode 3 ends]

100
00:05:25,393 --> 00:05:27,513
- Gosh.
- Help her.

101
00:05:27,513 --> 00:05:29,003
- Help her!
- Help her!

102
00:05:29,003 --> 00:05:30,383
Help her.

103
00:05:30,383 --> 00:05:33,323
Will the next episode play?

104
00:05:33,323 --> 00:05:34,863
Help her.

105
00:05:35,773 --> 00:05:37,793
That's a bit scary.

106
00:05:39,513 --> 00:05:41,783
The production crew is so cruel.

107
00:05:41,783 --> 00:05:44,213
They're putting me on edge.

108
00:05:44,213 --> 00:05:45,903
[Eyes locked in]

109
00:05:45,903 --> 00:05:48,313
- Gosh.
- Thank goodness.

110
00:05:48,313 --> 00:05:50,523
[Episode 4 is playing]

111
00:05:50,523 --> 00:05:52,283
Where did she run off to?

112
00:05:52,283 --> 00:05:54,643
Where did she run off to?

113
00:05:57,373 --> 00:05:58,933
Ji Han?

114
00:05:58,933 --> 00:06:01,243
What? Why are they together-

115
00:06:02,023 --> 00:06:07,403
Hold on. This is the perfect chance
to replace Lee Ye Na.

116
00:06:15,863 --> 00:06:18,253
What interesting timing.

117
00:06:20,623 --> 00:06:22,433
She took a shower.

118
00:06:23,113 --> 00:06:26,133
Oh, dear. My goodness.

119
00:06:26,133 --> 00:06:27,843
My goodness.

120
00:06:29,213 --> 00:06:31,853
Have a seat. You must have wounds.

121
00:06:33,033 --> 00:06:34,393
I can do this myself.

122
00:06:34,393 --> 00:06:35,723
Sit still.

123
00:06:35,723 --> 00:06:38,273
I'm not doing this because I like you.

124
00:06:38,273 --> 00:06:39,923
Gosh.

125
00:06:39,923 --> 00:06:41,533
She's badly injured.

126
00:06:42,153 --> 00:06:43,363
Shouldn't she go to the hospital?

127
00:06:43,363 --> 00:06:45,393
It's not what you think.

128
00:06:45,393 --> 00:06:46,913
I think I need to get going.

129
00:06:46,913 --> 00:06:49,773
I'm worried about my sister.
Most importantly, my parents-

130
00:06:51,093 --> 00:06:52,553
What?

131
00:06:53,613 --> 00:06:56,513
[Is the drama of passion reaching its peak?]

132
00:07:01,003 --> 00:07:02,943
What are you doing right now?

133
00:07:02,943 --> 00:07:05,993
Did he hit you? Is that why you ran away?

134
00:07:05,993 --> 00:07:07,513
I said it's not like that.

135
00:07:07,513 --> 00:07:10,483
- You don't have to worry.
- What has been going on, anyway?

136
00:07:10,483 --> 00:07:12,393
Why are you marrying a bastard like him?

137
00:07:12,393 --> 00:07:15,193
You should be living a good life
after leaving without a word like that.

138
00:07:15,193 --> 00:07:17,783
- What are you talking about?
- Why do you think...

139
00:07:17,783 --> 00:07:19,533
Why do you think I left this place?

140
00:07:19,533 --> 00:07:22,563
Do you even know how I felt
having to endure that?

141
00:07:25,373 --> 00:07:27,853
How did you feel?

142
00:07:27,853 --> 00:07:30,883
- How did you feel?
- I don't know! I want to know!

143
00:07:30,883 --> 00:07:34,783
I want to know how he felt!

144
00:07:34,783 --> 00:07:39,223
I'm a little worried.
I think it will be a matter of taste.

145
00:07:39,223 --> 00:07:42,103
[And the result is?]

146
00:07:43,483 --> 00:07:46,063
[Relieved]

147
00:07:46,063 --> 00:07:49,313
[Park So Rang's "Is this Marriage Valid?"
Episode 5]

148
00:07:49,313 --> 00:07:53,593
CEO, the Chairman is waiting for you.

149
00:07:54,363 --> 00:07:56,503
I'll be right back. Get some rest.

150
00:07:58,293 --> 00:08:00,393
CEO?

151
00:08:03,873 --> 00:08:05,793
Ye Na, where are you?

152
00:08:05,793 --> 00:08:08,113
I'm so worried. It's killing me.

153
00:08:11,373 --> 00:08:14,113
What happened? Why did you do that earlier?

154
00:08:14,113 --> 00:08:15,703
To be honest...

155
00:08:15,703 --> 00:08:19,333
I can't tell her. She'll be disappointed
if she finds out Ji Han helped me.

156
00:08:19,333 --> 00:08:21,333
Because they used to be a couple.

157
00:08:21,333 --> 00:08:23,943
I received a strange video.

158
00:08:25,793 --> 00:08:28,813
[Is she the other woman?]

159
00:08:28,813 --> 00:08:32,753
- Why would Tae Ju do such a thing?
- Does she not know?

160
00:08:32,753 --> 00:08:34,603
How can I with you?

161
00:08:36,123 --> 00:08:38,283
Can you do this when you're about to get married?

162
00:08:38,283 --> 00:08:40,163
Who did this?

163
00:08:40,163 --> 00:08:42,123
I think I should stop by home.

164
00:08:42,123 --> 00:08:45,123
My parents will understand me
if I tell them the truth.

165
00:08:45,123 --> 00:08:46,633
No!

166
00:08:48,243 --> 00:08:52,083
They must be shocked about what happened.

167
00:08:52,083 --> 00:08:55,433
I'll explain things to them.

168
00:08:56,803 --> 00:08:59,853
Se Ra, how can I repay you for this?

169
00:08:59,853 --> 00:09:01,833
Hey, don't be like that.

170
00:09:01,833 --> 00:09:03,653
We're friends like no other.

171
00:09:03,653 --> 00:09:07,353
Haven't we been friends for life
since our days at the orphanage?

172
00:09:07,353 --> 00:09:09,503
Thank you, Se Ra.

173
00:09:09,503 --> 00:09:11,403
We're just getting started, Ye Na.

174
00:09:11,403 --> 00:09:15,463
I'll destroy everything one by one,
without missing a single thing.

175
00:09:17,963 --> 00:09:19,493
Wow, we watched all of them.

176
00:09:19,493 --> 00:09:25,853
Park So Rang's short drama
"Is This Marriage Valid?" finished playing.

177
00:09:25,853 --> 00:09:29,093
I teared up while watching it.

178
00:09:29,093 --> 00:09:32,533
I remember everything that happened

179
00:09:32,533 --> 00:09:37,103
while working on this mission.

180
00:09:39,833 --> 00:09:44,473
So many people worked so hard
for this short drama.

181
00:09:45,683 --> 00:09:48,913
I had a lot of mixed feelings.

182
00:09:48,913 --> 00:09:51,433
I kept crying while I was watching.

183
00:09:53,683 --> 00:09:55,843
How do you feel?

184
00:09:55,843 --> 00:09:58,543
It's such a relief that it wasn't stopped.

185
00:09:58,543 --> 00:10:00,223
Thank you so much.

186
00:10:01,003 --> 00:10:03,103
Looks like she went through a lot.

187
00:10:03,103 --> 00:10:07,203
It's such a relief that we got to watch all of it.

188
00:10:07,203 --> 00:10:09,313
Competition shows are so cruel.

189
00:10:09,313 --> 00:10:12,013
- They are.
- What did the Five Stars think of this?

190
00:10:12,013 --> 00:10:16,423
While I was watching it, I thought
something familiar could be powerful.

191
00:10:16,423 --> 00:10:18,333
- It really is.
- It's scary.

192
00:10:18,333 --> 00:10:23,163
It felt so commonplace, yet...

193
00:10:23,163 --> 00:10:26,533
I kept begging for more.

194
00:10:26,533 --> 00:10:28,353
That's the hardest thing to pull off.

195
00:10:28,353 --> 00:10:33,213
Luring people in with something very familiar.

196
00:10:33,213 --> 00:10:38,473
It's so hard to do, but Director Park
seems to have a knack for it.

197
00:10:38,473 --> 00:10:39,513
Thank you.

198
00:10:39,513 --> 00:10:43,603
This kind of genre isn't really my thing.

199
00:10:43,603 --> 00:10:46,163
But...

200
00:10:47,313 --> 00:10:49,813
I'd like to recommend it to my mother.

201
00:10:49,813 --> 00:10:52,993
- She'll be shocked at the first scene.
- She'll like it.

202
00:10:52,993 --> 00:10:54,763
I think she'll love it.

203
00:10:54,763 --> 00:10:56,343
What a good son you are.

204
00:10:56,343 --> 00:10:58,233
[A good son who makes sure
his mother is entertained]

205
00:10:58,233 --> 00:11:01,113
Thank you so much, Director Park So Rang.

206
00:11:01,113 --> 00:11:02,473
This is a little...

207
00:11:02,473 --> 00:11:04,003
This isn't your thing.

208
00:11:04,003 --> 00:11:06,033
It's not plausible.

209
00:11:07,073 --> 00:11:09,313
Let's meet the next director.

210
00:11:09,313 --> 00:11:12,053
Master of absurd comedy
with a B-movie sensibility.

211
00:11:12,053 --> 00:11:13,983
Director Han Sang Il, please come forward.

212
00:11:13,983 --> 00:11:15,553
The master of absurd comedy.

213
00:11:16,493 --> 00:11:17,923
[Excited]

214
00:11:17,923 --> 00:11:19,693
I can't wait. I can't wait.

215
00:11:21,093 --> 00:11:23,323
It's finally the final round, Director Han.

216
00:11:23,323 --> 00:11:26,983
I was just hoping to avoid elimination in Round 1.

217
00:11:26,983 --> 00:11:29,603
I think all the luck I have will be spent here.

218
00:11:29,603 --> 00:11:33,603
I'm just hoping I'll continue to be lucky.

219
00:11:33,603 --> 00:11:38,493
In each round, you've been

220
00:11:38,493 --> 00:11:42,073
providing unforgettable images.

221
00:11:42,073 --> 00:11:44,633
In Round 1, there was the doghouse.

222
00:11:44,633 --> 00:11:48,633
In Round 2, it was the blowing of tissues.

223
00:11:48,633 --> 00:11:50,783
You've always had a unique focal point.

224
00:11:50,783 --> 00:11:55,483
Will there be funny scenes
in Episodes 3 to 5, too?

225
00:11:55,483 --> 00:11:59,863
Episodes 1 and 2 were mostly comedy.

226
00:11:59,863 --> 00:12:04,833
In Episode 3, it starts to become a thriller,
with twists involving the characters.

227
00:12:07,013 --> 00:12:09,753
Could you tell us the plot of Episodes 1 and 2?

228
00:12:09,753 --> 00:12:13,463
In Episodes 1 and 2, a woman named Ye Rin

229
00:12:13,463 --> 00:12:17,113
gets hit by a flying doghouse and goes
into a coma for three months.

230
00:12:17,113 --> 00:12:19,273
When she wakes up after three months,

231
00:12:19,273 --> 00:12:21,033
she has all the memories

232
00:12:21,033 --> 00:12:24,773
except for the ones of her boyfriend.

233
00:12:25,673 --> 00:12:27,503
Through Episodes 3 and 5,

234
00:12:27,503 --> 00:12:30,773
we see twists in the characters.

235
00:12:32,593 --> 00:12:35,403
What I'm a little worried about is

236
00:12:35,403 --> 00:12:40,183
that the story involves dialogue
and not a lot of action.

237
00:12:40,183 --> 00:12:44,453
It's about whether people would find it
interesting or boring.

238
00:12:44,453 --> 00:12:46,263
I think that's the key.

239
00:12:46,263 --> 00:12:47,923
[Focused]

240
00:12:47,923 --> 00:12:50,643
It must be so nerve-racking.

241
00:12:50,643 --> 00:12:52,683
[Nervous just to watch]

242
00:12:52,683 --> 00:12:54,343
[Will "My Love Story Only I Don't Know About"
get to play all the way to Episode 5?]

243
00:12:54,343 --> 00:12:56,973
["My Love Story Only I Don't Know About"]

244
00:12:56,973 --> 00:12:58,543
[Two years ago]

245
00:12:59,813 --> 00:13:01,023
JYP.

246
00:13:01,023 --> 00:13:02,643
Oh, my God.

247
00:13:04,073 --> 00:13:05,733
What is it, Team Leader? I'm busy.

248
00:13:05,733 --> 00:13:07,943
Ye Rin, I love you.

249
00:13:07,943 --> 00:13:10,173
Why do you talk nonsense every evening?

250
00:13:10,173 --> 00:13:12,123
How about we have a secret romance?

251
00:13:12,123 --> 00:13:14,243
There are different degrees of nonsense.

252
00:13:14,243 --> 00:13:16,973
If you utter another word,
we'll be seeing each other

253
00:13:16,973 --> 00:13:19,663
at the Labor Bureau, not the office.

254
00:13:19,663 --> 00:13:21,033
Okay, got it.

255
00:13:21,033 --> 00:13:22,993
I'll ask you out again next week.

256
00:13:23,813 --> 00:13:26,093
Don't do it, I said! Geez...

257
00:13:26,723 --> 00:13:28,653
This isn't my desk.

258
00:13:30,643 --> 00:13:32,533
Team Leader Kang Hyeon Su.

259
00:13:32,533 --> 00:13:36,873
He's popular, competent, and likable.
He's so annoying.

260
00:13:36,873 --> 00:13:40,253
Team Leader Kang Hyeon Su asked me out once.

261
00:13:40,253 --> 00:13:45,753
Why did I choose Gi Tak
over Team Leader Hyeon Su?

262
00:13:45,753 --> 00:13:49,643
Team Leader Hyeon Su is
definitely more attractive.

263
00:13:51,963 --> 00:13:54,343
I don't want to go to work.

264
00:13:58,683 --> 00:14:01,683
Hello, I'm Seo Gi Tak, Ye Rin's boyfriend.

265
00:14:01,683 --> 00:14:03,753
I heard a lot about you.

266
00:14:03,753 --> 00:14:06,963
I'm Ye Rin's co-worker, Kang Hyeon Su.

267
00:14:06,963 --> 00:14:10,903
Mr. Kang, I hope you no longer visit Ye Rin.

268
00:14:11,733 --> 00:14:13,633
Thank you for your understanding.

269
00:14:15,933 --> 00:14:17,243
Hey.

270
00:14:19,893 --> 00:14:22,833
I heard she doesn't even remember you.

271
00:14:28,483 --> 00:14:30,753
Huh? What's he doing?

272
00:14:30,753 --> 00:14:33,393
[The 10-second countdown starts]

273
00:14:33,393 --> 00:14:37,353
The next episode will play in four, three...

274
00:14:37,353 --> 00:14:40,183
[Please...]

275
00:14:42,183 --> 00:14:45,943
The countdown starts after one episode.

276
00:14:45,943 --> 00:14:49,183
It felt like time had stopped.

277
00:14:49,183 --> 00:14:53,873
[The countdown is amping up the nervousness]

278
00:14:53,873 --> 00:14:57,203
[Will the next episode play?]

279
00:14:58,623 --> 00:15:00,223
[Episode 4 plays]

280
00:15:00,223 --> 00:15:02,073
[What a relief]

281
00:15:02,073 --> 00:15:04,513
Have you been well the last week?

282
00:15:04,513 --> 00:15:07,313
Yes, there wasn't anything particularly wrong.

283
00:15:07,313 --> 00:15:10,903
Is your memory of your
dumb-looking boyfriend back?

284
00:15:10,903 --> 00:15:15,073
No, I only lost memories of Gi Tak.

285
00:15:15,073 --> 00:15:19,363
Strangely, I have all memories of other men.

286
00:15:19,363 --> 00:15:23,653
Something needs to keep happening,
not just dialogue.

287
00:15:23,653 --> 00:15:26,123
- It has to be nonstop.
- Strangely...

288
00:15:26,123 --> 00:15:30,363
Maybe your subconscious
doesn't want to remember him.

289
00:15:30,363 --> 00:15:31,133
Pardon?

290
00:15:31,133 --> 00:15:34,863
We can subconsciously erase the
memories we don't want to remember.

291
00:15:34,863 --> 00:15:37,343
Do you mean like a traumatic episode?

292
00:15:37,343 --> 00:15:41,333
Your memory could be sealed
even if it wasn't for trauma.

293
00:15:41,333 --> 00:15:42,703
It could be many things.

294
00:15:42,703 --> 00:15:45,653
You want to see another man.
You want to be in another man's arms.

295
00:15:45,653 --> 00:15:49,163
Or you want to eat with another man. I'm wondering

296
00:15:49,163 --> 00:15:52,033
if a thought like that could've erased Gi Tak.

297
00:15:52,033 --> 00:15:54,263
I'm not that kind of woman.

298
00:15:54,263 --> 00:15:55,873
That kind of woman?

299
00:15:55,873 --> 00:15:59,313
Wanting to see another man is a natural desire.

300
00:15:59,313 --> 00:16:01,553
I'm not a piece of trash like that.

301
00:16:01,553 --> 00:16:05,413
Please don't generalize because you're like that.

302
00:16:05,413 --> 00:16:06,683
Shit.

303
00:16:08,583 --> 00:16:10,833
[Finally got a laugh]

304
00:16:29,943 --> 00:16:31,443
What's the deal?

305
00:16:31,443 --> 00:16:34,193
Is it because the bed is uncomfortable?

306
00:16:44,623 --> 00:16:47,393
[Episode 4 ends]

307
00:16:47,393 --> 00:16:49,463
The genre suddenly changed.

308
00:16:49,463 --> 00:16:51,833
[Curious]

309
00:16:51,833 --> 00:16:54,833
[The two directors aren't showing reactions]

310
00:16:55,393 --> 00:16:59,243
[The countdown starts quietly]

311
00:17:00,213 --> 00:17:03,573
Please, please, please.

312
00:17:03,573 --> 00:17:05,213
[One last episode to go...]

313
00:17:09,773 --> 00:17:11,663
[Will it stop like this?]

314
00:17:11,663 --> 00:17:13,733
[Please]

315
00:17:14,223 --> 00:17:17,623
[Episode 5 plays]

316
00:17:17,623 --> 00:17:19,343
[Han Sang Il's "My Love Story
Only I Don't Know About" Episode 5]

317
00:17:19,343 --> 00:17:21,513
What are you doing?

318
00:17:21,513 --> 00:17:24,233
Well, I noticed you shuffling.

319
00:17:25,683 --> 00:17:29,073
Gosh, I suddenly need to poop urgently.

320
00:17:33,673 --> 00:17:35,273
What? What? What?

321
00:17:35,273 --> 00:17:37,433
He was a bad person.

322
00:17:37,433 --> 00:17:39,943
What's with him? He's so creepy.

323
00:17:46,283 --> 00:17:48,083
Are you scared of your boyfriend?

324
00:17:48,083 --> 00:17:50,783
Team Leader? What are you doing here?

325
00:17:50,783 --> 00:17:53,533
I left something when I was visiting you earlier.

326
00:17:53,533 --> 00:17:55,453
Why aren't you in your room?

327
00:17:55,453 --> 00:17:59,773
Well, I just wanted to get some fresh air.

328
00:18:06,903 --> 00:18:09,333
All of a sudden? What's the deal?

329
00:18:10,103 --> 00:18:12,703
Did you want me to embrace you like this?

330
00:18:13,453 --> 00:18:14,533
You should've said so.

331
00:18:14,533 --> 00:18:17,013
You're the one who pulled me.

332
00:18:17,013 --> 00:18:20,483
I thought you wanted to be in my arms.

333
00:18:20,483 --> 00:18:24,043
I think your tongue is
a little bit too well greased.

334
00:18:24,043 --> 00:18:26,753
[He likes the absurd humor]

335
00:18:26,753 --> 00:18:29,123
Just recover and return to work soon.

336
00:18:29,123 --> 00:18:32,523
Work is too boring without you.

337
00:18:34,523 --> 00:18:36,003
Okay, then.

338
00:18:43,223 --> 00:18:45,013
[Seo Gi Tak is fake]

339
00:18:48,843 --> 00:18:52,053
[Finished playing Episode 5]

340
00:18:52,053 --> 00:18:54,223
Shouldn't we watch the next episode?

341
00:18:54,223 --> 00:18:56,533
What does it mean? "Seo Gi Tak is fake"?

342
00:18:56,533 --> 00:18:57,873
[Impressed]

343
00:18:57,873 --> 00:18:59,733
Is Seo Gi Tak fake?

344
00:18:59,733 --> 00:19:00,793
That was good.

345
00:19:00,793 --> 00:19:02,833
Couldn't he just whisper that in her ear?

346
00:19:02,833 --> 00:19:03,913
I know.

347
00:19:03,913 --> 00:19:06,063
How does it feel to finish showing, Director Han?

348
00:19:06,063 --> 00:19:09,103
You wanted it more desperately than anyone.

349
00:19:09,103 --> 00:19:10,423
I just want to go to the end.

350
00:19:10,423 --> 00:19:13,143
That's all I thought of while waiting.

351
00:19:13,143 --> 00:19:15,493
I added a hook at the end of every episode.

352
00:19:15,493 --> 00:19:18,273
But it always happens at the end.

353
00:19:18,273 --> 00:19:21,243
I was worried people would
press stop before that.

354
00:19:21,243 --> 00:19:24,293
I was very anxious about the pacing.

355
00:19:24,293 --> 00:19:25,653
[Hmm...]

356
00:19:25,653 --> 00:19:27,893
In the beginning of each round,

357
00:19:27,893 --> 00:19:32,553
I saw something that I liked.
It was fun looking for them.

358
00:19:32,553 --> 00:19:35,043
But since you focused
on the story toward the end,

359
00:19:35,043 --> 00:19:39,593
it made me wonder if I'll ever see
those moments again.

360
00:19:39,593 --> 00:19:41,753
Without explaining enough,

361
00:19:41,753 --> 00:19:44,263
you switched or mixed genres.

362
00:19:44,263 --> 00:19:46,903
That got me flustered a bit.

363
00:19:46,903 --> 00:19:52,563
It felt confusing and chaotic instead of fun.

364
00:19:52,563 --> 00:19:54,663
I could tell you're a funny person.

365
00:19:54,663 --> 00:19:58,923
You find a way to make
ordinary things sound funny.

366
00:19:58,923 --> 00:20:03,783
But compared to your wit,
the characters or the story

367
00:20:03,783 --> 00:20:07,473
were a bit all over the place.

368
00:20:07,473 --> 00:20:10,813
I kept thinking I wasn't sure about this.

369
00:20:10,813 --> 00:20:13,653
I actually didn't mind the dialogue.

370
00:20:13,653 --> 00:20:15,303
But a lot of people were disappointed.

371
00:20:15,303 --> 00:20:19,303
I think I need to think about why that is.

372
00:20:19,983 --> 00:20:22,633
He won't allow any underdog's revolt.

373
00:20:22,633 --> 00:20:25,673
He was in first place in Round 1 and Round 2.

374
00:20:25,673 --> 00:20:27,923
He is a strong contender to win.

375
00:20:27,923 --> 00:20:30,873
Director Lee Yoo Jin, please come forward.

376
00:20:30,873 --> 00:20:32,233
I was curious about this.

377
00:20:32,233 --> 00:20:35,383
[Everyone's been waiting for him!]

378
00:20:35,383 --> 00:20:38,483
Hello, I've been acting for 12 years and...

379
00:20:38,483 --> 00:20:41,133
now a new director. I'm Lee Yoo Jin.

380
00:20:42,193 --> 00:20:45,193
I'm doing it in every possible way.

381
00:20:45,193 --> 00:20:49,113
[Milking the goats to afford tomorrow's shoot]

382
00:20:49,113 --> 00:20:51,203
Directors can't be afraid.

383
00:20:51,203 --> 00:20:54,213
You just go if you see a path.

384
00:20:54,213 --> 00:20:58,313
[In Round 1, he won first place with zero stops]

385
00:20:59,363 --> 00:21:01,333
[In Round 2's webtoon co-directing mission]

386
00:21:01,333 --> 00:21:03,663
[His team won first place again!]

387
00:21:03,663 --> 00:21:06,983
[He won Round 3's death match
by one vote difference]

388
00:21:07,423 --> 00:21:10,313
[Unstoppable 1st place director]

389
00:21:10,313 --> 00:21:13,333
Top 3 potential winners? Director Lee Yoo Jin?

390
00:21:13,333 --> 00:21:15,513
Director Lee Yoo Jin?

391
00:21:15,513 --> 00:21:19,263
Yoo Jin has been winning first place.

392
00:21:19,263 --> 00:21:22,493
I've constantly been keeping my eye on him.

393
00:21:22,493 --> 00:21:27,453
I'm curious how you feel
about being in the final round.

394
00:21:27,453 --> 00:21:30,713
I've been amazingly winning
first place every round.

395
00:21:30,713 --> 00:21:35,913
I don't think things have always
worked out for me in life.

396
00:21:35,913 --> 00:21:39,893
But this journey has been a little different.

397
00:21:39,893 --> 00:21:42,043
I want to thank my luck in life.

398
00:21:42,043 --> 00:21:44,833
You don't think things have
worked out for you in life?

399
00:21:44,833 --> 00:21:46,943
Being handsome has already helped you in life.

400
00:21:46,943 --> 00:21:48,563
You're right.

401
00:21:48,563 --> 00:21:50,293
Yes, you've always been blessed.

402
00:21:50,293 --> 00:21:52,773
The handsome ones don't know.

403
00:21:52,773 --> 00:21:55,463
Right, it's so hard to be born handsome.

404
00:21:55,463 --> 00:21:57,813
I'm jealous of his proportion.

405
00:21:57,813 --> 00:22:00,363
If I were there, you probably
could read the top line.

406
00:22:01,063 --> 00:22:02,053
Come on.

407
00:22:02,053 --> 00:22:04,283
He's covering up the title.

408
00:22:05,723 --> 00:22:08,963
You had cast Ko Chang Seok.

409
00:22:08,963 --> 00:22:10,613
He's much more senior than you.

410
00:22:10,613 --> 00:22:14,613
Did it feel uncomfortable
to direct him? Or maybe not?

411
00:22:14,613 --> 00:22:17,343
It wasn't as uncomfortable
as I thought it would be.

412
00:22:17,343 --> 00:22:23,453
The moment I felt like I could trust
the director in my acting career

413
00:22:23,453 --> 00:22:25,843
was when they had a clear picture,

414
00:22:25,843 --> 00:22:28,843
and they told me what was important.

415
00:22:28,843 --> 00:22:31,953
Then, I was able to depend on them as an actor.

416
00:22:31,953 --> 00:22:36,103
Since I knew to provide that clarity,

417
00:22:36,103 --> 00:22:38,793
I told him exactly what I wanted.

418
00:22:38,793 --> 00:22:43,673
So, it wasn't as difficult as expected.

419
00:22:43,673 --> 00:22:44,943
[Director Lee Yoo Jin is busy setting things up]

420
00:22:44,943 --> 00:22:47,673
We're moving things over there.

421
00:22:47,673 --> 00:22:49,933
[And Ko Chang Seok is looking at him]

422
00:22:49,933 --> 00:22:53,113
How do you feel seeing him direct?

423
00:22:53,113 --> 00:22:54,803
It's funny.

424
00:22:54,803 --> 00:22:57,503
[Kidding]

425
00:22:57,503 --> 00:22:59,303
I don't think I could do it.

426
00:23:00,013 --> 00:23:05,083
Short dramas have their own pacing and direction.

427
00:23:05,083 --> 00:23:07,233
But actors my age are slow-paced.

428
00:23:09,013 --> 00:23:11,713
I'll just do as he tells me to today.

429
00:23:11,713 --> 00:23:14,023
[Anticipating passionate acting]

430
00:23:14,523 --> 00:23:16,243
I'll say "Bam," then. Bam.

431
00:23:16,243 --> 00:23:18,413
React to the crashing noise.

432
00:23:18,413 --> 00:23:19,983
Here we go.

433
00:23:19,983 --> 00:23:21,223
Bam!

434
00:23:22,833 --> 00:23:26,433
Hey! My camera!

435
00:23:27,843 --> 00:23:30,023
- Cut!
- It's a cut.

436
00:23:30,023 --> 00:23:31,873
[Coughing]

437
00:23:31,873 --> 00:23:33,663
Give him some water.

438
00:23:34,463 --> 00:23:37,473
[The way Lee Yoo Jin works with a star actor]

439
00:23:37,473 --> 00:23:38,763
Cut, cut, cut!

440
00:23:38,763 --> 00:23:42,313
[Shouting]

441
00:23:42,313 --> 00:23:45,633
[Emotional acting]

442
00:23:45,633 --> 00:23:47,773
[Grabbing someone by the collar]

443
00:23:47,773 --> 00:23:49,183
Cut!

444
00:23:49,183 --> 00:23:51,723
Let's keep the first part short.

445
00:23:51,723 --> 00:23:54,393
We have to keep everything short.

446
00:23:56,163 --> 00:23:58,743
Do you think Director Lee Yoo Jin will win?

447
00:23:58,743 --> 00:24:01,083
That doesn't matter. He has to win.

448
00:24:01,083 --> 00:24:03,183
I'm working my ass off right now.

449
00:24:03,183 --> 00:24:04,913
[Didn't think it'd be this hard]

450
00:24:04,913 --> 00:24:08,033
Yoo Jin has to win and cast me.

451
00:24:08,773 --> 00:24:10,273
No, he should cast us.

452
00:24:10,273 --> 00:24:12,003
Thank you. Thank you.

453
00:24:12,003 --> 00:24:13,653
[Reserving his next project in advance]

454
00:24:13,653 --> 00:24:15,473
Say "Lee Yoo Jin, fighting" at the count
of three. One, two, three.

455
00:24:15,473 --> 00:24:17,343
Lee Yoo Jin, fighting!

456
00:24:19,383 --> 00:24:22,293
[It seemed like everything was going well...]

457
00:24:23,233 --> 00:24:26,183
[Talking noisily]

458
00:24:26,183 --> 00:24:30,573
[Something went wrong while filming?]

459
00:24:31,013 --> 00:24:33,613
[Serious]

460
00:24:34,973 --> 00:24:37,873
I think it's time to change the oil.

461
00:24:37,873 --> 00:24:38,823
[What's going on?]

462
00:24:38,823 --> 00:24:42,873
There is a product placement
scene in the episode.

463
00:24:42,873 --> 00:24:45,163
Instead of doing it subtly,

464
00:24:45,163 --> 00:24:49,413
I wanted to make it very, very, very blatant

465
00:24:49,413 --> 00:24:51,943
and make it comedic.

466
00:24:51,943 --> 00:24:53,503
I created a scene like that.

467
00:24:53,503 --> 00:24:56,753
[Shooting right now]

468
00:24:56,753 --> 00:24:59,803
[Serious voice]

469
00:24:59,803 --> 00:25:01,403
Do it like a real commercial.

470
00:25:01,403 --> 00:25:03,233
Give it a lot of contrast.

471
00:25:03,233 --> 00:25:05,403
This is the new stuff.

472
00:25:05,403 --> 00:25:07,203
[The new engine oil makes an appearance]

473
00:25:07,203 --> 00:25:08,763
This is...

474
00:25:09,963 --> 00:25:12,053
- Oil.
- Oil.

475
00:25:12,053 --> 00:25:14,013
[Very satisfied]

476
00:25:17,243 --> 00:25:20,813
[Director Lee Yoo Jin's final submission!]

477
00:25:21,693 --> 00:25:23,703
I'm so impressed with him.

478
00:25:23,703 --> 00:25:26,883
He does editing, mixing, and color correcting.

479
00:25:26,883 --> 00:25:30,493
I heard you did all the post-production work.

480
00:25:30,493 --> 00:25:34,693
For almost the entire week,

481
00:25:35,483 --> 00:25:37,273
I think I slept less than ten hours.

482
00:25:37,273 --> 00:25:39,933
It might be because I'm inexperienced.

483
00:25:39,933 --> 00:25:42,923
I was like, "Who would do all this if not me?"

484
00:25:42,923 --> 00:25:45,503
[He finished the final submission on his own]

485
00:25:45,503 --> 00:25:47,483
Do you have trouble trusting people?

486
00:25:47,483 --> 00:25:49,263
I think there's a bit of that, too.

487
00:25:49,263 --> 00:25:51,173
You'd rather do it even if it's hard.

488
00:25:51,173 --> 00:25:53,293
Since I've always been doing it on my own,

489
00:25:53,293 --> 00:25:55,223
I continued to do so.

490
00:25:55,223 --> 00:25:58,313
I feel bad because I can tell you're tired.

491
00:25:58,313 --> 00:25:59,553
I lost a lot of weight.

492
00:25:59,553 --> 00:26:01,733
Right, he looks very thin.

493
00:26:01,733 --> 00:26:04,203
Before we watch Episodes 3 to 5,

494
00:26:04,203 --> 00:26:07,783
please summarize Episodes 1 and 2 for us.

495
00:26:07,783 --> 00:26:12,983
An eccentric former actor turned
director, Yoo Jin's team

496
00:26:12,983 --> 00:26:15,953
gets a new assistant director, So Won.

497
00:26:15,953 --> 00:26:17,573
This is the story of her growth.

498
00:26:17,573 --> 00:26:20,153
They went to the same high school together.

499
00:26:20,153 --> 00:26:23,413
Yoo Jin was also her first love.

500
00:26:23,413 --> 00:26:29,313
The last episode ended with two suspicious
men walking toward them with a knife.

501
00:26:29,313 --> 00:26:32,763
In Episodes 3 to 5,

502
00:26:32,763 --> 00:26:36,553
there are AI, dopamine spikes,
and cameo appearances.

503
00:26:36,553 --> 00:26:40,713
A series of my secret weapons will be used.

504
00:26:40,713 --> 00:26:42,643
I can't do any more than this.

505
00:26:42,643 --> 00:26:47,523
I did my best. I hope I can
finish this feeling satisfied.

506
00:26:48,323 --> 00:26:52,723
Please play "Cast Them If You See the Path."

507
00:26:52,723 --> 00:26:57,133
[Will he be able to play all the way
through Episode 5?]

508
00:26:57,133 --> 00:27:00,533
[Cast Them If You See the Path]

509
00:27:00,533 --> 00:27:04,513
We have no budget. Why did you
add so many ridiculous scenes?

510
00:27:04,513 --> 00:27:08,413
The building explodes, and the
lead jumps off the building?

511
00:27:08,413 --> 00:27:10,313
Are you going to kill the actor?

512
00:27:10,313 --> 00:27:13,513
I'm that actor. The lead and the director.

513
00:27:13,513 --> 00:27:17,213
- I want you to catch me from down below.
- Oh, come on!

514
00:27:17,213 --> 00:27:20,613
We don't need production money. We have...

515
00:27:21,833 --> 00:27:23,663
AI.

516
00:27:26,073 --> 00:27:28,433
The day...

517
00:27:28,433 --> 00:27:31,313
I can do whatever I want...

518
00:27:31,313 --> 00:27:35,413
is finally here.

519
00:27:38,143 --> 00:27:40,103
- Wow.
- That's cute.

520
00:27:40,103 --> 00:27:43,103
He's utilizing the AI so well.

521
00:27:47,793 --> 00:27:50,233
Please come to your senses.

522
00:27:50,233 --> 00:27:53,083
People aren't moved no matter
how great technology is.

523
00:27:53,083 --> 00:27:55,763
The story is crappy. Who will find it moving?

524
00:27:55,763 --> 00:27:58,663
Hey, listen to you. Do you not want to get paid?

525
00:27:58,663 --> 00:28:00,743
But you don't pay me anyway.

526
00:28:01,473 --> 00:28:03,053
I don't get paid, either.

527
00:28:05,783 --> 00:28:07,623
We're almost done setting up.

528
00:28:07,623 --> 00:28:11,783
Okay. Should I use AI to make me look taller?

529
00:28:11,783 --> 00:28:15,463
One good thing about working with a crazy person

530
00:28:15,463 --> 00:28:20,683
is that I can briefly ignore my life
that was damaged beyond repair.

531
00:28:20,683 --> 00:28:22,723
- She had a secret.
- Let's do it in one go.

532
00:28:22,723 --> 00:28:24,363
Are they loan sharks?

533
00:28:24,363 --> 00:28:26,103
This will be fun.

534
00:28:27,213 --> 00:28:34,423
I briefly forgot that my reality was cold hell.

535
00:28:34,423 --> 00:28:35,963
What's going on?

536
00:28:37,763 --> 00:28:39,603
No!

537
00:28:40,393 --> 00:28:42,213
[Episode 3 ends right before she gets stabbed]

538
00:28:42,213 --> 00:28:44,463
Come on, seriously?

539
00:28:44,463 --> 00:28:46,603
We must watch what happens next.

540
00:28:46,603 --> 00:28:48,623
- Wow.
- What was that?

541
00:28:48,623 --> 00:28:50,763
He ended in a perfect moment.

542
00:28:50,763 --> 00:28:53,433
That's a good strategy.

543
00:28:53,433 --> 00:28:56,723
- You can't do this.
- Show me the rest.

544
00:28:56,723 --> 00:28:59,453
Three, two, one.

545
00:29:00,503 --> 00:29:01,493
[Episode 4 plays]

546
00:29:01,493 --> 00:29:02,873
How do you feel?

547
00:29:03,593 --> 00:29:04,923
How do you feel?

548
00:29:04,923 --> 00:29:06,993
You can tell it's an expensive one, right?

549
00:29:10,873 --> 00:29:13,353
Why are you taking it too far?

550
00:29:13,353 --> 00:29:14,753
Pardon?

551
00:29:14,753 --> 00:29:16,853
How did it feel?

552
00:29:18,013 --> 00:29:19,553
You're in.

553
00:29:21,023 --> 00:29:22,483
Give me. Give me. Give me.

554
00:29:22,483 --> 00:29:24,743
Where did you get this? It looks so real.

555
00:29:24,743 --> 00:29:26,783
It's a rubber knife. Daebak.

556
00:29:26,783 --> 00:29:29,713
My film school classmate works
for the prop department.

557
00:29:29,713 --> 00:29:32,003
I asked him to get me one, Director.

558
00:29:32,003 --> 00:29:33,493
- Good work!
- Yes, sir!

559
00:29:33,493 --> 00:29:35,123
I said we can get equipment.

560
00:29:35,123 --> 00:29:37,813
That's not the problem right now.

561
00:29:37,813 --> 00:29:41,913
Director, the actress who is helping us
with the test shoot is here.

562
00:29:41,913 --> 00:29:43,853
Really? Okay, let's get started then.

563
00:29:43,853 --> 00:29:46,263
- Give me the bag.
- Yes, Cinematographer.

564
00:29:46,263 --> 00:29:48,323
- Is the gimbal in Yoo Jin's car?
- No, I brought it here.

565
00:29:48,323 --> 00:29:50,963
How did you get the actress? Is she your friend?

566
00:29:50,963 --> 00:29:52,723
She's my girlfriend.

567
00:29:52,723 --> 00:29:54,143
- What? Why?
- What?

568
00:29:54,143 --> 00:29:54,933
- Girlfriend?
- Who is?

569
00:29:54,933 --> 00:29:56,283
- Seriously?
- There must've been a reason.

570
00:29:56,283 --> 00:29:57,623
- But you're losing hair.
- You've got to be kidding.

571
00:29:57,623 --> 00:29:58,503
So annoying.

572
00:29:58,503 --> 00:30:00,913
[The viewers like it]

573
00:30:02,603 --> 00:30:03,723
- It's a man, huh?
- You have jaundice.

574
00:30:03,723 --> 00:30:05,203
- Shut up.
- How did it happen?

575
00:30:05,203 --> 00:30:06,593
Give me the knife.

576
00:30:07,393 --> 00:30:09,023
What the heck...

577
00:30:15,833 --> 00:30:17,483
Director, I think...

578
00:30:18,203 --> 00:30:20,663
I'm working on an independent film.

579
00:30:22,713 --> 00:30:27,823
Director, could I borrow your equipment
since this is such a coincidence?

580
00:30:27,823 --> 00:30:30,203
Does your head still hurt these days?

581
00:30:30,703 --> 00:30:32,423
[LOL]

582
00:30:32,423 --> 00:30:34,003
Director, I...

583
00:30:34,653 --> 00:30:36,483
Let's cancel the shoot today.

584
00:30:37,273 --> 00:30:41,373
[Episode 4 ends while they were enjoying it]

585
00:30:42,013 --> 00:30:43,353
[Whining]

586
00:30:43,353 --> 00:30:45,573
[Everyone seems to want more]

587
00:30:45,573 --> 00:30:48,223
[Will Episode 5 play?]

588
00:30:48,223 --> 00:30:51,463
This is the worst moment. Feels like
the countdown is too slow.

589
00:30:52,203 --> 00:30:55,413
[Time seems to have slowed down]

590
00:30:55,933 --> 00:30:58,083
[Hurry up, next episode]

591
00:30:58,083 --> 00:31:00,123
What if it doesn't play?

592
00:31:00,123 --> 00:31:01,803
[Will it play or stop?]

593
00:31:02,613 --> 00:31:04,733
[Episode 5 starts]

594
00:31:04,733 --> 00:31:06,863
[What a relief]

595
00:31:09,703 --> 00:31:12,973
Director thinks we can shoot
with the industrial equipment today.

596
00:31:12,973 --> 00:31:15,173
Do you still believe what he says?

597
00:31:16,003 --> 00:31:20,283
I don't, but he does unbelievable things at times.

598
00:31:20,283 --> 00:31:22,423
- Miracles.
- Guys!

599
00:31:23,103 --> 00:31:25,773
Guys, the director lent me a camera!

600
00:31:25,773 --> 00:31:27,293
Let's shoot all we want...

601
00:31:27,293 --> 00:31:29,713
"We make the path by walking."

602
00:31:29,713 --> 00:31:33,033
- We might call it a miracle when a chance is
- What's that? A camera?

603
00:31:33,033 --> 00:31:35,553
given to someone who's not at all prepared.

604
00:31:35,553 --> 00:31:40,363
But he'll probably say everything was planned.

605
00:31:40,363 --> 00:31:44,473
If there's a miracle, it'll probably look like that...

606
00:31:45,673 --> 00:31:47,183
Oh, my gosh!

607
00:31:47,183 --> 00:31:49,423
[Save the camera]

608
00:31:49,423 --> 00:31:52,023
Gosh, that's too much.

609
00:31:54,483 --> 00:31:56,143
Crazy bastard.

610
00:31:59,853 --> 00:32:01,433
She should've caught the camera.

611
00:32:01,433 --> 00:32:04,393
I know. She should've caught the camera!

612
00:32:04,393 --> 00:32:06,683
Oppa, are you okay?

613
00:32:06,683 --> 00:32:08,883
- Oppa?
- Oppa?

614
00:32:08,883 --> 00:32:10,283
Oppa?

615
00:32:11,223 --> 00:32:12,583
Are you hurt?

616
00:32:12,583 --> 00:32:14,373
Are you okay, Oppa?

617
00:32:14,373 --> 00:32:16,143
Hold on!

618
00:32:17,103 --> 00:32:20,043
- Do you know how much this is?
- Everyone, quiet!

619
00:32:22,063 --> 00:32:23,183
The camera is in shock.

620
00:32:23,183 --> 00:32:26,043
I can piece it together and suture it back.

621
00:32:26,043 --> 00:32:27,873
I can put it together if I look closely.

622
00:32:27,873 --> 00:32:29,353
Taking it apart will make things worse.

623
00:32:29,353 --> 00:32:30,423
- Right?
- Yes.

624
00:32:30,423 --> 00:32:32,013
I won't take it apart.

625
00:32:32,013 --> 00:32:34,193
Okay, thanks-

626
00:32:35,753 --> 00:32:37,023
You don't know how to fix it, do you?

627
00:32:37,023 --> 00:32:39,173
Precisely. Are you a doctor?

628
00:32:39,173 --> 00:32:41,553
I'm a director, you bastard!

629
00:32:42,223 --> 00:32:45,463
We laughed, cried,

630
00:32:46,243 --> 00:32:50,473
and fought hard on our summer days.

631
00:32:50,473 --> 00:32:52,203
["Cast Them If You See the Path"]

632
00:32:52,203 --> 00:32:55,193
[You can watch the full version on Lehzin Snack]

633
00:32:57,383 --> 00:32:59,303
Director Lee Yoo Jin.

634
00:33:00,613 --> 00:33:06,273
You used AI so brilliantly.

635
00:33:06,273 --> 00:33:09,513
- It felt so refreshing.
- It was fun.

636
00:33:09,513 --> 00:33:13,483
And the AI Ko Chang Seok was good, too.

637
00:33:13,483 --> 00:33:14,903
Wasn't that AI?

638
00:33:14,903 --> 00:33:16,543
Was he real?

639
00:33:16,543 --> 00:33:18,073
[Ko Chang Seok was not created by AI]

640
00:33:18,073 --> 00:33:19,003
Cut, okay.

641
00:33:19,003 --> 00:33:21,433
I enjoyed it a lot, too.

642
00:33:21,433 --> 00:33:25,333
I got a lot of positive energy from it.

643
00:33:25,333 --> 00:33:27,313
I enjoyed it.

644
00:33:27,313 --> 00:33:28,953
Thank you.

645
00:33:28,953 --> 00:33:33,163
Not just in short dramas,

646
00:33:33,163 --> 00:33:36,993
but also in films or a long series,

647
00:33:36,993 --> 00:33:42,733
you'll become a valuable director
in Korea, Director Lee Yoo Jin.

648
00:33:42,733 --> 00:33:44,223
Welcome.

649
00:33:45,063 --> 00:33:47,253
- That was a huge compliment.
- Thank you.

650
00:33:47,253 --> 00:33:49,653
Since this is the last round,

651
00:33:49,653 --> 00:33:55,663
I'm starting to get excited for
some reason. It's a problem.

652
00:33:55,663 --> 00:33:58,513
As for what I wish for...

653
00:33:58,513 --> 00:34:01,363
I would like to win first place.

654
00:34:01,363 --> 00:34:04,433
Watching his series, I thought,

655
00:34:04,433 --> 00:34:07,083
"That's something I could never do."

656
00:34:07,083 --> 00:34:08,983
Because the genre is totally different.

657
00:34:08,983 --> 00:34:12,033
But I don't want to lose.

658
00:34:12,793 --> 00:34:15,093
It got me thinking, "I want to win."

659
00:34:15,093 --> 00:34:16,883
I hope I can win.

660
00:34:16,883 --> 00:34:19,173
A talented director who's dominating

661
00:34:19,173 --> 00:34:22,883
the short drama scene in China and now in Korea

662
00:34:22,883 --> 00:34:25,943
Director Lee Dong Hun, please come forward.

663
00:34:29,443 --> 00:34:31,903
- Hello.
- Yes, Director Lee Dong Hun.

664
00:34:31,903 --> 00:34:34,593
I heard you used all your connections.

665
00:34:34,593 --> 00:34:38,573
My elementary, middle, and high
school classmates appeared as extras.

666
00:34:38,573 --> 00:34:41,703
And a dentist I know also appeared.

667
00:34:41,703 --> 00:34:43,373
[He used everyone he knows]

668
00:34:43,373 --> 00:34:45,443
You must know many good people.

669
00:34:45,443 --> 00:34:47,493
You've lived a good life.

670
00:34:47,493 --> 00:34:50,923
I came this far thanks
to my connections. I'm grateful.

671
00:34:50,923 --> 00:34:53,003
Will we be able to see your friends?

672
00:34:53,003 --> 00:34:54,613
The dentists and classmates.

673
00:34:54,613 --> 00:34:58,413
They were supposed to be in
Episodes 1 and 2, but it didn't work.

674
00:34:58,413 --> 00:35:02,063
- Someone else will be in Episode 3.
- Got it.

675
00:35:03,153 --> 00:35:05,533
We'll be looking for his friend,
whom we don't know.

676
00:35:06,513 --> 00:35:12,143
Please summarize Episodes 1 and 2
before we watch Episode 3.

677
00:35:12,143 --> 00:35:17,193
The beggar couple, Cheon Won Man and Ju Se Yeong,

678
00:35:17,193 --> 00:35:20,353
go to a chaebol party to scam big time

679
00:35:20,353 --> 00:35:23,393
and seduce a chaebol's daughter.

680
00:35:24,493 --> 00:35:28,073
Director Lee Dong Hun's work
is very short-form-like.

681
00:35:28,073 --> 00:35:32,183
My drama is very short-form-like as well.

682
00:35:32,183 --> 00:35:35,313
I think people might compare us.

683
00:35:35,313 --> 00:35:38,533
Since I came this far, I might as well

684
00:35:38,533 --> 00:35:43,783
get into the Top 3 and
be acknowledged as a director.

685
00:35:43,783 --> 00:35:46,303
["The Beggar Couple Joins the Chaebol Family"]

686
00:35:46,303 --> 00:35:48,033
[Lee Dong Hun's "The Beggar Couple
Joins the Chaebol Family" Episode 3]

687
00:35:48,033 --> 00:35:49,733
CEO.

688
00:35:49,733 --> 00:35:52,063
- What are you doing?
- What?

689
00:35:53,063 --> 00:35:56,453
Oh, right. You're that girl.

690
00:35:56,453 --> 00:35:58,663
The one who poured wine on me.

691
00:36:00,013 --> 00:36:03,813
- Earlier, I was...
- Gosh...

692
00:36:03,813 --> 00:36:05,403
What are you doing?

693
00:36:05,403 --> 00:36:07,623
You shouldn't have messed with me, then.

694
00:36:07,623 --> 00:36:09,693
This is your lucky day.

695
00:36:10,913 --> 00:36:12,643
Let go. Let go of this.

696
00:36:12,643 --> 00:36:13,693
Let go of me!

697
00:36:13,693 --> 00:36:15,833
Let go of this and talk.

698
00:36:15,833 --> 00:36:17,513
Enough.

699
00:36:20,053 --> 00:36:22,553
Sisters shouldn't fight like this.

700
00:36:23,323 --> 00:36:26,143
- This is...
- Se Yeong, my long-lost daughter.

701
00:36:26,143 --> 00:36:27,803
I've been looking for you for a long time.

702
00:36:27,803 --> 00:36:30,103
You are a member of the Oh family starting today.

703
00:36:30,103 --> 00:36:31,503
- What happened?
- Pardon?

704
00:36:31,503 --> 00:36:32,943
Daddy?

705
00:36:33,683 --> 00:36:35,423
- Huh?
- Sisters?

706
00:36:35,423 --> 00:36:37,573
Without any proof?

707
00:36:37,573 --> 00:36:39,833
How does this work?

708
00:36:39,833 --> 00:36:42,013
[Will this help him or hurt him?]

709
00:36:43,723 --> 00:36:46,753
I'm your long-lost daughter, Chairman?

710
00:36:46,753 --> 00:36:50,113
Ever since I lost you
as a little girl at the beach,

711
00:36:50,113 --> 00:36:52,743
I looked for you all my life.

712
00:36:52,743 --> 00:36:55,053
- I finally found you.
- How could this be?

713
00:36:55,053 --> 00:36:58,383
Forget about your past and live as Oh Se Yeong.

714
00:36:58,383 --> 00:37:00,593
I would love to.

715
00:37:00,593 --> 00:37:04,443
Can he live with me, by the way?

716
00:37:04,443 --> 00:37:06,583
Are you two married?

717
00:37:06,583 --> 00:37:09,673
- No, no. Not at all.
- No, no. Not at all.

718
00:37:09,673 --> 00:37:11,243
The thing is,

719
00:37:11,243 --> 00:37:14,173
he's like an older brother to me.

720
00:37:14,173 --> 00:37:17,033
I've never thought about being apart from him.

721
00:37:17,033 --> 00:37:18,373
Sure.

722
00:37:18,373 --> 00:37:21,863
It's the least I can do for someone
who took care of my Se Yeong.

723
00:37:21,863 --> 00:37:25,603
Will I become Oh Won Man*, then?
(Sounds like "five won only")

724
00:37:25,603 --> 00:37:27,743
[What's this?]

725
00:37:27,743 --> 00:37:32,093
Will the next episode play?

726
00:37:32,093 --> 00:37:34,143
I think it will.

727
00:37:34,143 --> 00:37:35,563
I'm sure.

728
00:37:35,563 --> 00:37:39,253
But the story is unfolding too abruptly.

729
00:37:39,253 --> 00:37:43,513
Those ten seconds were so hellish.

730
00:37:43,513 --> 00:37:47,603
- One.
- Oh Man Won!

731
00:37:47,603 --> 00:37:49,683
Under one condition.

732
00:37:49,683 --> 00:37:52,143
[Relieved]

733
00:37:52,143 --> 00:37:57,473
I'll observe you for a year to see
if you are worthy of joining the family.

734
00:37:57,473 --> 00:38:02,253
If you successfully convince me,
I'll adopt you as my child.

735
00:38:02,253 --> 00:38:05,523
Thank you for giving me a chance!

736
00:38:05,523 --> 00:38:07,303
Thank you.

737
00:38:10,293 --> 00:38:14,063
Oppa, I've never seen such a big house.

738
00:38:14,063 --> 00:38:16,303
After working so hard,
a day like this has finally come.

739
00:38:16,303 --> 00:38:19,363
We... We've made it. Right?

740
00:38:23,433 --> 00:38:26,723
Change into these clothes, sir and ma'am.

741
00:38:26,723 --> 00:38:28,103
- Ma'am?
- Sir?

742
00:38:28,103 --> 00:38:31,533
- Pinch my cheek, Oppa.
- Your cheek?

743
00:38:34,093 --> 00:38:35,563
This is real.

744
00:38:35,563 --> 00:38:38,013
Are we smooth sailing from now on?

745
00:38:38,013 --> 00:38:40,333
Bloody smooth sailing.

746
00:38:40,333 --> 00:38:42,073
Okay!

747
00:38:44,013 --> 00:38:47,063
Who says you're my family?

748
00:38:47,063 --> 00:38:52,913
I've never acknowledged you,
beggars, as my family.

749
00:38:52,913 --> 00:38:55,273
Amy is pulling all the weight.

750
00:38:55,273 --> 00:38:58,053
She's good at acting.

751
00:38:58,053 --> 00:39:01,223
Unni, I hope we get along going forward.

752
00:39:01,223 --> 00:39:03,973
We're sisters after all. We should get along.

753
00:39:03,973 --> 00:39:05,903
Hey, give me a break.

754
00:39:05,903 --> 00:39:07,903
I'm not your sister.

755
00:39:10,493 --> 00:39:12,863
What a temper.

756
00:39:12,863 --> 00:39:15,603
She's really something.

757
00:39:16,323 --> 00:39:21,033
This is all well and good, but why
do I have to share a room with you?

758
00:39:21,033 --> 00:39:24,103
Darn it. You are being pampered, thanks to me.

759
00:39:24,103 --> 00:39:25,773
Do you want to get kicked out?

760
00:39:25,773 --> 00:39:27,863
[Episode 4 ends]

761
00:39:28,583 --> 00:39:30,153
[Quiet]

762
00:39:30,153 --> 00:39:31,783
What will happen?

763
00:39:31,783 --> 00:39:34,083
Hurry, hurry.

764
00:39:35,023 --> 00:39:37,293
- Aren't they a couple?
- Aren't they?

765
00:39:38,043 --> 00:39:39,963
Are they not getting along?

766
00:39:39,963 --> 00:39:41,723
Hurry, hurry, hurry.

767
00:39:41,723 --> 00:39:44,993
Will we be able to see Episode 5?

768
00:39:45,793 --> 00:39:47,923
Huh? What?

769
00:39:50,283 --> 00:39:53,113
[The video ended before Episode 5 played]

770
00:39:53,113 --> 00:39:54,623
Gosh...

771
00:39:54,623 --> 00:39:58,083
- I could see it coming.
- Really?

772
00:39:58,083 --> 00:39:59,103
[Hmm...]

773
00:39:59,103 --> 00:40:03,533
Director Lee Dong Hun,
unfortunately, the next episode...

774
00:40:03,533 --> 00:40:07,703
- Is this how it goes?
- will not be playing.

775
00:40:07,703 --> 00:40:09,093
So cruel.

776
00:40:09,853 --> 00:40:11,413
It's cruel, but that's the rule, everyone.

777
00:40:11,413 --> 00:40:16,953
Let's see how many stops
Director Lee Dong Hun got.

778
00:40:16,953 --> 00:40:18,613
Please reveal.

779
00:40:18,613 --> 00:40:20,653
Gosh, terrible people.

780
00:40:22,583 --> 00:40:24,513
[Director Lee Dong Hun got 36 stops]

781
00:40:24,513 --> 00:40:26,053
It's a shame.

782
00:40:26,053 --> 00:40:32,293
Director Lee Dong Hun will
be eliminated with 36 stops.

783
00:40:32,293 --> 00:40:35,213
I heard he made many short dramas.

784
00:40:35,213 --> 00:40:39,883
But fewer than 3% of Koreans
have watched a short drama.

785
00:40:39,883 --> 00:40:41,803
That means it's a tiny market.

786
00:40:41,803 --> 00:40:46,473
I thought it was a formula limited to 3%.

787
00:40:46,473 --> 00:40:49,663
This is how the video gets stopped.

788
00:40:49,663 --> 00:40:51,003
- It's pretty cruel.
- By the way,

789
00:40:51,003 --> 00:40:56,013
- you can tell if it's going to play or not.
- How so?

790
00:40:56,013 --> 00:40:58,613
- You know when the red bar moves?
- When the bar moves?

791
00:40:58,613 --> 00:41:01,763
- People usually were like, "What? No!"

792
00:41:01,763 --> 00:41:03,643
But they were quiet.

793
00:41:03,643 --> 00:41:06,793
You can easily tell from that.

794
00:41:06,793 --> 00:41:09,463
You get judged by just the reaction.

795
00:41:09,463 --> 00:41:11,643
- It gives you an idea.
- It does.

796
00:41:11,643 --> 00:41:13,393
That's even scarier.

797
00:41:13,393 --> 00:41:16,863
The unrelenting nature of short dramas

798
00:41:16,863 --> 00:41:19,773
comes from being shocking, provocative, or fun.

799
00:41:19,773 --> 00:41:24,993
It has to feel like that,
but it fizzled out instead.

800
00:41:24,993 --> 00:41:28,463
It felt like it was getting lost as it progressed.

801
00:41:28,463 --> 00:41:31,273
So, it felt boring.

802
00:41:31,273 --> 00:41:36,543
I started feeling that I didn't have
to watch the next episode.

803
00:41:36,543 --> 00:41:38,783
That's how I felt. It's a shame.

804
00:41:38,783 --> 00:41:40,863
I'm disappointed. So disappointed.

805
00:41:40,863 --> 00:41:46,583
The fact that it was stopped was upsetting, too.

806
00:41:46,583 --> 00:41:51,043
But the judges and the viewers were

807
00:41:51,043 --> 00:41:53,593
feeling bored like I was.

808
00:41:53,593 --> 00:41:58,083
I realized I was lacking a lot.
It was too sloppy.

809
00:41:58,083 --> 00:42:02,953
I'd like to create and direct
many more short dramas

810
00:42:02,953 --> 00:42:07,823
that are hits going forward.

811
00:42:08,593 --> 00:42:11,363
Let's meet the next director.

812
00:42:11,363 --> 00:42:16,193
She got extra attention because
she resembles Shin Sae Kyeong.

813
00:42:16,193 --> 00:42:18,213
The Bong Joon Ho of the BL genre.

814
00:42:18,213 --> 00:42:21,713
- You're pressuring her right now.
- I was curious about hers.

815
00:42:21,713 --> 00:42:23,113
[Pressured]

816
00:42:23,803 --> 00:42:25,753
The descriptions are so fancy.

817
00:42:25,753 --> 00:42:28,493
The Bong Joon Ho of BL
who resembles Shin Sae Kyeong.

818
00:42:28,493 --> 00:42:32,973
It takes two celebrities to describe
Director Yang Gyeong Hee.

819
00:42:32,973 --> 00:42:36,013
It's finally the final. How do you feel?

820
00:42:36,013 --> 00:42:40,303
I can't believe I'm in the final right now.

821
00:42:40,303 --> 00:42:42,033
It's a directing competition,

822
00:42:42,033 --> 00:42:46,313
but I'm realizing again that
a director can't do it alone.

823
00:42:46,313 --> 00:42:52,433
I'd like to thank my crew and actors once again.

824
00:42:52,433 --> 00:42:56,203
We worked hard on the next three episodes.

825
00:42:56,203 --> 00:42:58,303
[Excited cheers]

826
00:42:58,303 --> 00:43:01,423
Will your specialty, BL, be featured?

827
00:43:01,423 --> 00:43:06,513
The character, Ddol Ddol,
is like kimchi in this series.

828
00:43:06,513 --> 00:43:10,033
He adds spiciness whenever it gets too rich.

829
00:43:10,033 --> 00:43:12,823
It's not exactly BL,

830
00:43:12,823 --> 00:43:16,673
but Ddol Ddol thinks he's in love.

831
00:43:16,673 --> 00:43:19,473
So, I think that makes it the BL.

832
00:43:19,473 --> 00:43:21,443
[Min Ji and Ddol Ddol's apartment]

833
00:43:21,443 --> 00:43:24,453
You should get closer to be in the same frame.

834
00:43:24,453 --> 00:43:26,803
Come up off to the side like this.

835
00:43:26,803 --> 00:43:29,223
Yes, that's it. That's it.

836
00:43:29,223 --> 00:43:33,013
I didn't try to make this a BL scene.

837
00:43:33,013 --> 00:43:40,713
I hope the transition from horror
to comedy comes through.

838
00:43:40,713 --> 00:43:43,353
[Acting their hearts out]

839
00:43:44,013 --> 00:43:46,723
[Totally satisfied]

840
00:43:47,403 --> 00:43:49,543
[A break for the hardworking actors]

841
00:43:49,543 --> 00:43:51,273
[Kimchi pancake party]

842
00:43:52,963 --> 00:43:56,533
They cook them on an iron griddle.

843
00:43:56,533 --> 00:43:58,243
They're so crispy.

844
00:43:58,243 --> 00:43:59,743
[Nice and crispy]

845
00:43:59,743 --> 00:44:01,163
[Sizzling, kimchi pancakes' heartbeat]

846
00:44:01,163 --> 00:44:03,283
There's a lot of kimchi in it, too.

847
00:44:03,283 --> 00:44:05,163
It's good kimchi.

848
00:44:05,163 --> 00:44:07,863
[What's the plot of the first two episodes?]

849
00:44:07,863 --> 00:44:10,523
It's about Joseon's King Lee Hyeon
landing in Hongdae

850
00:44:10,523 --> 00:44:14,663
and meets the MZ-er Min Ji and
unemployed gay man Ddol Ddol.

851
00:44:14,663 --> 00:44:19,203
People find out that Lee Hyeon looks exactly like

852
00:44:19,203 --> 00:44:23,713
top celebrity Lee Do Yun, and they chase him.

853
00:44:23,713 --> 00:44:26,133
We'll start the judging now.

854
00:44:26,133 --> 00:44:28,223
Play the video.

855
00:44:29,243 --> 00:44:32,903
I'm worried about Lee Dong Hun
and Park So Rang's,

856
00:44:32,903 --> 00:44:35,773
but I feel like I could beat them
for some reason.

857
00:44:35,773 --> 00:44:38,813
The genre must play a big part.

858
00:44:38,813 --> 00:44:41,473
I'll beat everyone and win 100 million won.

859
00:44:41,473 --> 00:44:43,693
["Joseon Man, MZ Woman, and a Gay Man"]

860
00:44:43,693 --> 00:44:52,233
[Yang Gyeong Hee's "Joseon Man,
MZ Woman, and a Gay Man" Episode 3]

861
00:44:52,233 --> 00:44:53,403
Get your hands off me.

862
00:44:53,403 --> 00:44:55,083
You are a very rude woman.

863
00:44:55,083 --> 00:44:57,043
How many times do you have to touch my face?

864
00:44:57,043 --> 00:44:59,953
What? You almost died, and I saved you.

865
00:44:59,953 --> 00:45:02,153
What kind of show is this, by the way?

866
00:45:02,153 --> 00:45:04,313
Is it a hidden camera? Explain right now.

867
00:45:04,313 --> 00:45:06,523
What have you been saying all this time?

868
00:45:06,523 --> 00:45:07,943
I cannot understand you.

869
00:45:07,943 --> 00:45:11,383
Anyway, I have no place to stay here.
I need lodging.

870
00:45:11,383 --> 00:45:13,993
Why are you so proud when you are homeless?

871
00:45:13,993 --> 00:45:16,153
Why don't you show me the money first?

872
00:45:16,153 --> 00:45:17,433
Money?

873
00:45:18,213 --> 00:45:19,463
I have no money.

874
00:45:19,463 --> 00:45:21,893
[Isn't this a bit slow?]

875
00:45:25,233 --> 00:45:27,643
These are all I have right now.

876
00:45:33,373 --> 00:45:35,833
[No reactions to Ddol Ddol's appearance]

877
00:45:41,663 --> 00:45:43,343
You bitches!

878
00:45:43,343 --> 00:45:45,193
You used me as bait.

879
00:45:45,193 --> 00:45:47,743
Hey, hey, hey.

880
00:45:51,673 --> 00:45:52,643
[Reacting to gold]

881
00:45:52,643 --> 00:45:55,083
Are these real? Do you have
rent money this month?

882
00:45:55,083 --> 00:45:56,983
Of course not.

883
00:45:56,983 --> 00:46:00,443
- Nice to meet you, customer.
- We're here to protect you.

884
00:46:00,443 --> 00:46:04,353
- It's like the goose...
- That lays golden eggs.

885
00:46:04,353 --> 00:46:06,653
[Episode 3 ends in one location]

886
00:46:06,653 --> 00:46:08,523
[Will Episode 4 play?]

887
00:46:08,523 --> 00:46:12,083
Five, four, three, two...

888
00:46:12,083 --> 00:46:14,223
[Silence]

889
00:46:14,223 --> 00:46:15,933
- One.
- I'm nervous.

890
00:46:15,933 --> 00:46:18,123
There's very little reaction.

891
00:46:19,523 --> 00:46:22,233
What if the video stops?

892
00:46:22,233 --> 00:46:25,463
[Suffocating countdown]

893
00:46:26,173 --> 00:46:28,223
[Will it stop like this?]

894
00:46:28,223 --> 00:46:30,253
- You bastard!
- Geez.

895
00:46:30,253 --> 00:46:32,493
[Episode 4 is playing]

896
00:46:33,113 --> 00:46:34,553
You cannot!

897
00:46:34,553 --> 00:46:35,943
Men and women should be separated.

898
00:46:35,943 --> 00:46:37,993
A man and a woman cannot live together.

899
00:46:37,993 --> 00:46:40,073
Oppa, I'm a woman, too.

900
00:46:40,073 --> 00:46:41,673
Bring me bedding.

901
00:46:41,673 --> 00:46:43,173
Do you not have a guest room?

902
00:46:43,173 --> 00:46:45,223
You want to share the guest room with me?

903
00:46:45,223 --> 00:46:47,013
Come on.

904
00:46:47,013 --> 00:46:51,553
And how am I supposed to sleep
in a place that's like a shed?

905
00:46:51,553 --> 00:46:54,283
Listen to you. A shed?

906
00:46:54,283 --> 00:46:56,493
Are you calling our place a shed?

907
00:46:56,493 --> 00:46:59,273
Tons of people can't even
afford a place like this.

908
00:46:59,273 --> 00:47:01,753
Is it because you're a king?
You have zero social skills.

909
00:47:01,753 --> 00:47:04,163
Hey, stop yelling at him. He's handsome.

910
00:47:04,163 --> 00:47:05,873
Take a shower first, Oppa.
Let me remove your robe.

911
00:47:05,873 --> 00:47:08,663
Ddol Ddol, why are you doing this? I am scared.

912
00:47:08,663 --> 00:47:10,783
I'm a man. We're the same gender.

913
00:47:10,783 --> 00:47:12,923
- Do not do this.
- You talk too much!

914
00:47:12,923 --> 00:47:13,903
Do not do this.

915
00:47:13,903 --> 00:47:15,013
[No men allowed]

916
00:47:21,093 --> 00:47:22,923
Look at his eyelashes.

917
00:47:22,923 --> 00:47:25,583
It's like a traditional ink painting.

918
00:47:25,583 --> 00:47:28,763
Look at his skin. Who's your dermatologist?

919
00:47:28,763 --> 00:47:30,373
You're driving me wild.

920
00:47:30,373 --> 00:47:31,943
"Driving me wild."

921
00:47:31,943 --> 00:47:33,523
"Driving me wild."

922
00:47:33,523 --> 00:47:35,003
[Ddol Ddol is adding some flavor]

923
00:47:35,003 --> 00:47:37,293
[Cracking up]

924
00:47:46,993 --> 00:47:49,693
Lady, I need you to protect me.

925
00:47:49,693 --> 00:47:50,793
Huh?

926
00:47:50,793 --> 00:47:54,143
[Will the romance start?]

927
00:48:02,143 --> 00:48:03,933
[Will we see the romance?]

928
00:48:03,933 --> 00:48:08,063
Will the next episode play?

929
00:48:08,063 --> 00:48:10,353
[Can't play Episode 5
if there are more than 34 stops]

930
00:48:11,733 --> 00:48:14,123
[Director Yang Gyeong Hee's journey]

931
00:48:14,123 --> 00:48:16,303
[Will it end here?]

932
00:48:16,303 --> 00:48:18,063
Huh?

933
00:48:18,063 --> 00:48:19,363
Huh?

934
00:48:21,063 --> 00:48:23,763
I just wanted to play Episode 5.

935
00:48:23,763 --> 00:48:26,073
I need to show them Episode 5.

936
00:48:28,123 --> 00:48:29,983
[Episode 5 is playing]

937
00:48:30,443 --> 00:48:32,923
[Relieved]

938
00:48:32,923 --> 00:48:38,803
[Yang Gyeong Hee's "Joseon Man,
MZ Woman, and a Gay Man" Episode 5]

939
00:48:38,803 --> 00:48:42,813
Do you want to fall in the middle
of Hongdae again?

940
00:48:42,813 --> 00:48:44,923
I do not, Ddol Ddol. It's my fault-

941
00:48:44,923 --> 00:48:46,853
Kim Min Ji!

942
00:48:46,853 --> 00:48:49,303
Do you want to miss rent and
sleep in the hallway again?

943
00:48:49,303 --> 00:48:50,303
No.

944
00:48:50,303 --> 00:48:54,003
Who said you could come up on my bed? You...

945
00:48:54,003 --> 00:48:55,613
scared me.

946
00:48:55,613 --> 00:48:57,143
Are you guys crazy?

947
00:48:57,143 --> 00:48:59,533
Get off. Get off each other right now.

948
00:48:59,533 --> 00:49:03,193
How dare you act lovey-dovey
in front of me right now?

949
00:49:03,193 --> 00:49:05,173
Sit straight.

950
00:49:05,173 --> 00:49:06,793
Seriously.

951
00:49:07,753 --> 00:49:09,483
You're flipping my pancakes.

952
00:49:09,483 --> 00:49:12,363
We'll all sleep together from now on.
I'm sleeping in the middle.

953
00:49:12,363 --> 00:49:13,703
Okay.

954
00:49:16,613 --> 00:49:20,443
Actor Lee Do Yun was found
passed out in his home.

955
00:49:20,443 --> 00:49:24,223
He was sent to the hospital,
and he is currently in a coma.

956
00:49:24,223 --> 00:49:26,783
Could he have attempted suicide?

957
00:49:26,783 --> 00:49:29,123
It happened at dawn today.

958
00:49:29,123 --> 00:49:31,313
I knew it was strange.

959
00:49:31,313 --> 00:49:33,663
He fell from the sky.

960
00:49:33,663 --> 00:49:35,983
And he only says weird things.

961
00:49:36,813 --> 00:49:41,413
By chance, do you believe in reincarnation?

962
00:49:45,063 --> 00:49:47,233
[Lukewarm reaction]

963
00:49:47,233 --> 00:49:48,693
[Mysterious expression]

964
00:49:48,693 --> 00:49:53,353
All of Director Yang Gyeong Hee's
episodes were played.

965
00:49:54,343 --> 00:49:56,223
I can't be satisfied.

966
00:49:56,223 --> 00:50:01,073
I don't know how many votes I got yet.

967
00:50:01,073 --> 00:50:03,413
[The viewers' expressions are mysterious]

968
00:50:03,413 --> 00:50:05,963
It's not my kind of thing.

969
00:50:05,963 --> 00:50:07,933
I know it was well done.

970
00:50:07,933 --> 00:50:09,213
He pressed it.

971
00:50:09,213 --> 00:50:10,773
The result...

972
00:50:10,773 --> 00:50:15,723
I thought it grew weaker as it progressed.

973
00:50:16,563 --> 00:50:21,793
Of course, Ddol Ddol added fun moments.

974
00:50:21,793 --> 00:50:24,483
Do you want to fall in the middle
of Hongdae again?

975
00:50:24,483 --> 00:50:26,563
[The side character was
like a breath of fresh air]

976
00:50:26,563 --> 00:50:28,663
Kim Min Ji!

977
00:50:28,663 --> 00:50:31,743
But it fizzled out as it went on.

978
00:50:31,743 --> 00:50:34,863
I thought about why that was.

979
00:50:34,863 --> 00:50:37,163
It's a series with continuity.

980
00:50:37,163 --> 00:50:40,543
I watched with a smile
because the characters are cute.

981
00:50:40,543 --> 00:50:43,563
I wish it had happened as part
of a story progression.

982
00:50:43,563 --> 00:50:46,283
The comedy the character brought was separate

983
00:50:46,283 --> 00:50:50,443
from the story's progression toward the end.

984
00:50:50,443 --> 00:50:52,593
If those two things were combined,

985
00:50:52,593 --> 00:50:56,773
people wouldn't have thought
it was slow and boring.

986
00:50:56,773 --> 00:50:58,693
It's hard for me to predict.

987
00:50:58,693 --> 00:51:01,893
I thought it was very well done.

988
00:51:01,893 --> 00:51:05,963
The judges' opinion was very different from mine.

989
00:51:05,963 --> 00:51:09,393
I don't know how many votes I'm going to get.

990
00:51:09,393 --> 00:51:11,883
That concerns me a bit.

991
00:51:12,813 --> 00:51:16,333
It's down to the last director now.

992
00:51:16,333 --> 00:51:21,223
He's the Na Hong Jin of short drama
with a distinctive thriller style.

993
00:51:21,223 --> 00:51:23,843
Director Lee Joo Seung, please come forward.

994
00:51:23,843 --> 00:51:26,473
[Lee Joo Seung's "The Murderer Upstairs"]

995
00:51:26,473 --> 00:51:27,843
[Excited]

996
00:51:27,843 --> 00:51:30,943
We have Bong Joon Ho and
Na Hong Jin of short dramas.

997
00:51:30,943 --> 00:51:33,463
- We've got them all.
- What a lineup.

998
00:51:34,643 --> 00:51:36,413
I wish I could turn this off.

999
00:51:36,413 --> 00:51:37,843
It's so scary.

1000
00:51:37,843 --> 00:51:39,583
It's taking up all three screens.

1001
00:51:39,583 --> 00:51:41,913
I didn't know Yoon So Yi could be this scary.

1002
00:51:41,913 --> 00:51:45,063
- She's not a ghost.
- I'm too scared to say anything.

1003
00:51:45,893 --> 00:51:48,433
- It's so scary when it's blown up like that.
- Really.

1004
00:51:48,433 --> 00:51:49,953
What a poster.

1005
00:51:49,953 --> 00:51:52,093
You're in the final round.

1006
00:51:52,093 --> 00:51:55,963
And you even entered the final
as the first-place winner.

1007
00:51:55,963 --> 00:51:57,433
How do you feel?

1008
00:51:57,433 --> 00:51:59,673
I'm so happy.

1009
00:51:59,673 --> 00:52:03,283
So many people helped me.

1010
00:52:03,283 --> 00:52:06,863
I'm so relieved that
I won't be disappointing them.

1011
00:52:06,863 --> 00:52:09,503
[Director Lee Joo Seung received three stops]

1012
00:52:09,503 --> 00:52:10,703
Look at Director Han's expression.

1013
00:52:10,703 --> 00:52:13,513
[He stunned Director Han Soo Ji]

1014
00:52:13,513 --> 00:52:15,003
And the result is!

1015
00:52:15,003 --> 00:52:17,773
[He won by 48-stop difference]

1016
00:52:18,223 --> 00:52:20,673
[He became the rising dark horse]

1017
00:52:20,673 --> 00:52:24,993
The director I'm keeping the
closest eye on is Joo Seung.

1018
00:52:24,993 --> 00:52:28,503
His first two episodes were so shocking...

1019
00:52:28,503 --> 00:52:30,913
He really geared up for it.

1020
00:52:30,913 --> 00:52:31,643
So...

1021
00:52:31,643 --> 00:52:32,933
[It won't be easy...]

1022
00:52:32,933 --> 00:52:37,163
I was like, "What? What happened to him?"

1023
00:52:37,163 --> 00:52:40,853
He became so good all of a sudden.

1024
00:52:40,853 --> 00:52:46,593
You chose Director Lee Yoo Jin
as your biggest threat.

1025
00:52:46,593 --> 00:52:47,903
Right, I can see why.

1026
00:52:47,903 --> 00:52:52,623
Director Lee Yoo Jin has been
getting good results.

1027
00:52:52,623 --> 00:52:55,523
Are you concerned about it at all?

1028
00:52:55,523 --> 00:53:00,633
Since we are direct junior and senior,

1029
00:53:00,633 --> 00:53:03,523
it can't be avoided. We're both actors, too.

1030
00:53:03,523 --> 00:53:05,203
And I enjoyed his series a lot.

1031
00:53:05,203 --> 00:53:09,463
I know he is way more talented than I am.

1032
00:53:09,463 --> 00:53:11,193
So, I'm keeping an eye on him.

1033
00:53:11,193 --> 00:53:12,933
You made a thriller short drama.

1034
00:53:12,933 --> 00:53:16,133
Do you still not regret choosing that genre?

1035
00:53:16,133 --> 00:53:18,753
No, I don't regret it.

1036
00:53:18,753 --> 00:53:23,303
I always liked movies that happen in one location.

1037
00:53:23,303 --> 00:53:28,073
It started with me wondering
if it'd work on the viewers.

1038
00:53:28,073 --> 00:53:33,023
I'm not sure if it will, but I worked hard on it.

1039
00:53:33,023 --> 00:53:35,343
Actually, there is...

1040
00:53:35,343 --> 00:53:40,703
a low-budget feature film script
I worked on for a long time.

1041
00:53:40,703 --> 00:53:43,103
I worked on it for about four years.

1042
00:53:43,103 --> 00:53:46,653
I thought the production would
start, but it got canceled.

1043
00:53:46,653 --> 00:53:49,823
Because the film industry was slowing down.

1044
00:53:49,823 --> 00:53:52,863
I think the lack of trust in me contributed, too.

1045
00:53:52,863 --> 00:53:58,603
So, I hope this series helps me
earn people's trust.

1046
00:53:58,603 --> 00:54:02,933
It's my dream to be reborn
as a trustworthy director.

1047
00:54:02,933 --> 00:54:07,923
I hope being on this show does that for me.

1048
00:54:08,693 --> 00:54:12,913
Please summarize the first two
episodes before we start Episode 3.

1049
00:54:12,913 --> 00:54:18,223
In the first two episodes,
a best-selling author, Jeong Wu's

1050
00:54:18,223 --> 00:54:21,313
career is about to end because
he doesn't have a second book.

1051
00:54:21,313 --> 00:54:25,853
But he happens to overhear the
new upstairs neighbor's murder.

1052
00:54:25,853 --> 00:54:31,413
He wrote that as a synopsis,
and the publisher liked it.

1053
00:54:31,413 --> 00:54:35,353
He realizes he needs to report her.
While he is calling 911,

1054
00:54:35,353 --> 00:54:38,193
the neighbor visits him, and that's how it ended.

1055
00:54:39,013 --> 00:54:42,223
Doesn't it look like she's saying,
"I'll kill you if you vote"?

1056
00:54:42,223 --> 00:54:43,943
And not a murderer upstairs?

1057
00:54:43,943 --> 00:54:48,443
It looks like she'll kill me
if I press the button.

1058
00:54:48,443 --> 00:54:50,603
I'm scared, but we'll start the video.

1059
00:54:50,603 --> 00:54:52,513
Play the video.

1060
00:54:52,513 --> 00:54:54,963
[Legs shaking]

1061
00:54:55,343 --> 00:54:58,303
Can he secure his spot in first place?

1062
00:54:58,303 --> 00:55:00,283
[Extremely nervous]

1063
00:55:01,793 --> 00:55:06,743
They spoke very highly of the first two episodes.

1064
00:55:06,743 --> 00:55:10,133
Do you know what the big problem is?

1065
00:55:10,133 --> 00:55:12,883
I'm more confident in Episodes 3 to 5.

1066
00:55:13,913 --> 00:55:15,863
[Game over]

1067
00:55:15,863 --> 00:55:17,613
Finally.

1068
00:55:17,613 --> 00:55:19,953
[Feeling threatened]

1069
00:55:19,953 --> 00:55:23,133
["The Murderer Upstairs"]

1070
00:55:23,133 --> 00:55:25,633
[Lee Joo Seung's
"The Murderer Upstairs" Episode 3]

1071
00:55:25,633 --> 00:55:27,833
Yes, go ahead.

1072
00:55:29,333 --> 00:55:30,573
This is unfair.

1073
00:55:30,573 --> 00:55:32,003
The apartment upstairs...

1074
00:55:32,003 --> 00:55:33,963
Yes, the apartment upstairs.

1075
00:55:33,963 --> 00:55:35,753
Speak calmly.

1076
00:55:36,953 --> 00:55:39,303
I called the wrong number.
I didn't mean to call the police.

1077
00:55:39,303 --> 00:55:41,573
Tap on the speaker if something is going on.

1078
00:55:41,573 --> 00:55:44,083
I'm really okay. I'll hang up.

1079
00:55:46,533 --> 00:55:47,903
Who's there?

1080
00:55:48,613 --> 00:55:50,253
I'm your upstairs neighbor.

1081
00:55:50,253 --> 00:55:52,073
Just one second.

1082
00:56:03,893 --> 00:56:05,323
Hello.

1083
00:56:05,323 --> 00:56:07,253
I'm disappointed.

1084
00:56:07,253 --> 00:56:10,033
- What do you mean?
- We met yesterday.

1085
00:56:10,033 --> 00:56:12,703
But you asked who I was just now.

1086
00:56:12,703 --> 00:56:15,713
I'm out of it since I didn't get any sleep.

1087
00:56:15,713 --> 00:56:19,563
Oh, you were home.

1088
00:56:19,563 --> 00:56:22,253
I guess you don't work these days.

1089
00:56:22,253 --> 00:56:24,923
I work at home.

1090
00:56:24,923 --> 00:56:26,853
I'm here to get the plate back.

1091
00:56:27,523 --> 00:56:30,093
The plate? Right.

1092
00:56:30,093 --> 00:56:32,473
Give me a moment. I haven't done the dishes.

1093
00:56:32,473 --> 00:56:34,273
You can do them quickly, right?

1094
00:56:34,853 --> 00:56:36,103
Pardon?

1095
00:56:36,103 --> 00:56:37,653
I'll wait.

1096
00:56:38,623 --> 00:56:41,003
I'll bring it to you quickly.

1097
00:56:45,633 --> 00:56:48,473
[Scary]

1098
00:56:50,693 --> 00:56:53,333
You don't mind me waiting inside, right?

1099
00:56:53,333 --> 00:56:56,123
[Episode 3 ends at a crucial moment]

1100
00:56:56,543 --> 00:56:59,373
[So curious]

1101
00:56:59,373 --> 00:57:01,083
Don't let her in.

1102
00:57:01,083 --> 00:57:03,103
No, don't let her in.

1103
00:57:03,103 --> 00:57:07,543
Will the next episode play?

1104
00:57:09,613 --> 00:57:10,863
[Episode 4 is playing]

1105
00:57:10,863 --> 00:57:12,693
Sure.

1106
00:57:12,693 --> 00:57:15,783
Then, pardon me.

1107
00:57:17,873 --> 00:57:20,333
Did you like the cake?

1108
00:57:20,333 --> 00:57:21,563
Yes, it was delicious.

1109
00:57:21,563 --> 00:57:24,903
I should give you something in return. I'm sorry.

1110
00:57:24,903 --> 00:57:28,303
Let's see each other often.
It's a scary world these days.

1111
00:57:28,303 --> 00:57:30,263
Neighbors should stick together.

1112
00:57:30,263 --> 00:57:31,583
Okay.

1113
00:57:32,813 --> 00:57:34,543
By the way,

1114
00:57:36,623 --> 00:57:38,403
is there something...

1115
00:57:40,733 --> 00:57:42,613
in your pocket?

1116
00:57:42,613 --> 00:57:43,893
Pardon?

1117
00:57:45,233 --> 00:57:48,313
You've been keeping your hand in your pocket.

1118
00:57:49,403 --> 00:57:51,603
Acting is so important.

1119
00:57:51,603 --> 00:57:54,633
It's a knife. I must've put it there
after opening a package.

1120
00:57:54,633 --> 00:57:56,043
I see.

1121
00:57:56,763 --> 00:57:58,653
I'm prying too much, aren't I?

1122
00:57:58,653 --> 00:57:59,883
I'm sorry.

1123
00:57:59,883 --> 00:58:02,733
No, it could have looked dangerous.

1124
00:58:02,733 --> 00:58:06,343
I don't like it when things aren't clear
since I'm a single woman.

1125
00:58:06,343 --> 00:58:08,923
I'm the same way. It's a scary world.

1126
00:58:09,803 --> 00:58:10,973
So...

1127
00:58:10,973 --> 00:58:12,333
[Focused]

1128
00:58:12,333 --> 00:58:14,853
did you really enjoy the cake?

1129
00:58:14,853 --> 00:58:18,273
Did you make it yourself?
I thought it was from a store.

1130
00:58:18,273 --> 00:58:19,973
Wow.

1131
00:58:20,593 --> 00:58:22,783
It was my first time making it.

1132
00:58:23,893 --> 00:58:25,733
Wasn't it too fishy?

1133
00:58:28,083 --> 00:58:29,953
Why would a cake be fishy?

1134
00:58:31,433 --> 00:58:33,693
It had something special in it.

1135
00:58:34,773 --> 00:58:36,173
Like what?

1136
00:58:37,793 --> 00:58:39,033
It's a secret.

1137
00:58:39,033 --> 00:58:41,553
[The intense Episode 4 ends]

1138
00:58:41,553 --> 00:58:43,633
- Wow.
- He's too good.

1139
00:58:43,633 --> 00:58:44,993
It's like a movie.

1140
00:58:45,563 --> 00:58:50,813
All right, will the next episode play?

1141
00:58:50,813 --> 00:58:52,253
Will it?

1142
00:58:52,973 --> 00:58:55,143
[Please, please]

1143
00:58:56,983 --> 00:58:58,593
Is it not playing?

1144
00:58:59,503 --> 00:59:01,163
Is it not playing?

1145
00:59:02,113 --> 00:59:05,443
[Really?]

1146
00:59:06,483 --> 00:59:07,953
Is it not playing?

1147
00:59:07,953 --> 00:59:09,963
- It can't be.
- Geez.

1148
00:59:09,963 --> 00:59:11,583
I'm a pharmacist.

1149
00:59:11,583 --> 00:59:14,783
I took over a pharmacy nearby and moved here.

1150
00:59:15,773 --> 00:59:17,413
I'm a pharmacist.

1151
00:59:17,413 --> 00:59:19,773
I took over a pharmacy nearby and moved here.

1152
00:59:19,773 --> 00:59:21,723
It's opening next week.

1153
00:59:21,723 --> 00:59:22,943
What do you do?

1154
00:59:22,943 --> 00:59:26,013
I'm an office worker. It's not
something anyone would know about.

1155
00:59:26,013 --> 00:59:28,153
Are you married?

1156
00:59:28,153 --> 00:59:29,943
I got divorced three years ago.

1157
00:59:29,943 --> 00:59:31,163
I see.

1158
00:59:31,163 --> 00:59:33,093
You have a daughter.

1159
00:59:33,093 --> 00:59:35,173
Does she live with you?

1160
00:59:36,263 --> 00:59:38,913
We just met. Why are you so inquisitive?

1161
00:59:38,913 --> 00:59:40,233
I want to get to know you.

1162
00:59:40,233 --> 00:59:42,403
It's making me a bit uncomfortable.

1163
00:59:42,403 --> 00:59:43,493
Good job. Good job.

1164
00:59:43,493 --> 00:59:45,333
I'm sorry.

1165
00:59:45,333 --> 00:59:47,513
I wasn't trying to get you to apologize.

1166
00:59:47,513 --> 00:59:50,983
I'm still sorry.

1167
00:59:51,913 --> 00:59:53,503
Shit.

1168
00:59:53,503 --> 00:59:55,173
[Whoa!]

1169
00:59:56,943 --> 01:00:00,573
- Well, then...
- Don't you have any questions for me?

1170
01:00:00,573 --> 01:00:03,493
- This is crazy.
- Anything you're curious about?

1171
01:00:03,493 --> 01:00:04,703
Daebak.

1172
01:00:04,703 --> 01:00:06,543
We can take our time getting to know each other.

1173
01:00:06,543 --> 01:00:09,753
Gosh, it sounded like you were flirting.

1174
01:00:09,753 --> 01:00:12,163
"We can take our time."

1175
01:00:14,023 --> 01:00:15,483
I got the chills.

1176
01:00:16,173 --> 01:00:19,783
I'll make sure to offer you something next time.

1177
01:00:19,783 --> 01:00:22,963
Gosh, this is so annoying.

1178
01:00:22,963 --> 01:00:24,303
Pardon?

1179
01:00:26,453 --> 01:00:30,193
You aren't interested in me because I'm old, huh?

1180
01:00:30,193 --> 01:00:31,833
Is that how it is?

1181
01:00:32,463 --> 01:00:34,703
No, i-it's not like that.

1182
01:00:34,703 --> 01:00:36,843
Yes, that's it.

1183
01:00:39,763 --> 01:00:42,303
Aren't you curious about me?

1184
01:00:44,013 --> 01:00:47,053
[You can watch the full version on Lehzin Snack]

1185
01:00:48,943 --> 01:00:51,073
[What a tease]

1186
01:00:51,073 --> 01:00:53,303
[Is it already over?]

1187
01:00:53,303 --> 01:00:54,673
I want to know what happens next.

1188
01:00:54,673 --> 01:00:56,273
I want to know.

1189
01:00:56,273 --> 01:00:58,263
That was good.

1190
01:00:59,203 --> 01:01:01,123
Seriously.

1191
01:01:01,123 --> 01:01:02,823
- What a strange woman.
- You got sucked in again.

1192
01:01:02,823 --> 01:01:04,793
- She's a strange woman.
- She was just acting.

1193
01:01:04,793 --> 01:01:07,023
- A very strange woman.
- That was Yoon So Yi.

1194
01:01:07,023 --> 01:01:12,613
I know her, but I thought,
"Was she always like that?"

1195
01:01:12,613 --> 01:01:15,043
- That's right.
- It was so impressive.

1196
01:01:15,043 --> 01:01:18,913
It was as if she'd come here
and kill us if it were stopped.

1197
01:01:18,913 --> 01:01:21,283
- No one can press the button.
- She was so scary.

1198
01:01:21,283 --> 01:01:23,253
It made me forget the rule.

1199
01:01:23,253 --> 01:01:26,113
I was sure it was going to be played.

1200
01:01:26,113 --> 01:01:30,443
While I was watching his work,

1201
01:01:30,443 --> 01:01:34,113
I realized a short drama can show such intensity

1202
01:01:34,113 --> 01:01:36,573
just by two people acting in one location.

1203
01:01:36,573 --> 01:01:41,273
The acting was totally immaculate.

1204
01:01:41,273 --> 01:01:44,273
I think it was very well made.

1205
01:01:44,273 --> 01:01:48,993
It's all thanks to your directing abilities.

1206
01:01:48,993 --> 01:01:50,353
While watching it,

1207
01:01:50,353 --> 01:01:54,213
I thought if "The Murderer Upstairs"
were streaming

1208
01:01:54,213 --> 01:01:57,443
and it was paid content, I would pay to watch it.

1209
01:01:57,443 --> 01:02:02,323
I'd have faith in you and set it up
as an automatic payment.

1210
01:02:02,323 --> 01:02:05,273
It was so intense and entertaining.

1211
01:02:05,273 --> 01:02:08,453
I think I'd pay to watch it, too.

1212
01:02:08,453 --> 01:02:10,533
I enjoyed it a lot.

1213
01:02:10,533 --> 01:02:14,073
It was intense, and the acting was excellent.

1214
01:02:14,073 --> 01:02:17,653
I think it will have an edge against anything.

1215
01:02:17,653 --> 01:02:19,713
I thought it was very powerful.

1216
01:02:19,713 --> 01:02:21,523
I enjoyed it a lot.

1217
01:02:22,473 --> 01:02:25,593
I wondered if a thriller short drama could work

1218
01:02:25,593 --> 01:02:28,213
and if slow-paced content would work.

1219
01:02:28,213 --> 01:02:33,033
I've been asking that question
without compromising.

1220
01:02:33,033 --> 01:02:37,193
And I was told that it worked.

1221
01:02:37,193 --> 01:02:41,803
That already was an answer to my question.

1222
01:02:41,803 --> 01:02:44,303
That comment was the most memorable for me.

1223
01:02:44,303 --> 01:02:46,633
[Final round results]

1224
01:02:46,633 --> 01:02:48,573
[Out of seven directors]

1225
01:02:50,303 --> 01:02:52,893
[Only six directors survived]

1226
01:02:52,893 --> 01:02:55,363
[3rd place: A compact cinema
camera set for pro filmmakers]

1227
01:02:55,363 --> 01:02:57,473
[2nd place: 50 million won]

1228
01:02:57,473 --> 01:03:00,163
[1st place: 100 million won]

1229
01:03:00,163 --> 01:03:01,973
[Who will be the winner?]

1230
01:03:01,973 --> 01:03:05,283
We are only awaiting the
announcement of the final winner.

1231
01:03:05,283 --> 01:03:09,423
These directors played all five episodes
despite the harsh votes.

1232
01:03:09,423 --> 01:03:13,463
Please welcome the
potential winners to the stage.

1233
01:03:13,463 --> 01:03:16,033
[Final ranking announcement]

1234
01:03:16,033 --> 01:03:18,323
[Excited]

1235
01:03:18,323 --> 01:03:21,893
You overcame the pressure of not
being able to play the next episode

1236
01:03:21,893 --> 01:03:24,523
and successfully finished the race.

1237
01:03:26,113 --> 01:03:29,363
I'm worried that I started getting my hopes up.

1238
01:03:29,993 --> 01:03:33,873
I had flashbacks of my storyline.

1239
01:03:33,873 --> 01:03:36,913
This is the final announcement.

1240
01:03:36,913 --> 01:03:41,223
We have a very big prize, don't we?

1241
01:03:41,223 --> 01:03:42,083
It's 100 million won.

1242
01:03:42,083 --> 01:03:46,923
The first-place director will win 500 million-

1243
01:03:46,923 --> 01:03:48,363
500 million?

1244
01:03:48,363 --> 01:03:50,503
Are you paying them an extra 400 million?

1245
01:03:50,503 --> 01:03:51,883
I said the wrong thing.

1246
01:03:51,883 --> 01:03:53,813
You really are the prince of Asia.

1247
01:03:53,813 --> 01:03:55,313
We would love that.

1248
01:03:55,313 --> 01:03:58,543
- Let's all split it.
- Sounds good.

1249
01:03:58,543 --> 01:04:00,533
[Oops...]

1250
01:04:01,363 --> 01:04:04,933
- Eighty million each wouldn't be bad.
- Sounds good!

1251
01:04:04,933 --> 01:04:08,153
Okay, so...

1252
01:04:08,153 --> 01:04:09,973
I had this thought.

1253
01:04:09,973 --> 01:04:13,713
People often ask what
you'd do with the prize money.

1254
01:04:13,713 --> 01:04:15,703
It's a common question.

1255
01:04:15,703 --> 01:04:21,273
After watching your work
and talking to each one of you,

1256
01:04:21,273 --> 01:04:25,063
I became certain that you'll definitely

1257
01:04:25,063 --> 01:04:29,583
invest that money into your projects.

1258
01:04:29,583 --> 01:04:36,033
It will give you a chance to reinvest
in order to expand your world.

1259
01:04:36,033 --> 01:04:39,423
This was a very meaningful show in that regard.

1260
01:04:39,423 --> 01:04:43,053
[Director's Arena was that much more meaningful]

1261
01:04:44,693 --> 01:04:47,593
Here's the moment of truth.

1262
01:04:47,593 --> 01:04:52,453
Based on the average viewing time
of the series that finished playing,

1263
01:04:52,453 --> 01:04:54,933
the final ranking will be determined.

1264
01:04:54,933 --> 01:05:00,413
I'll reveal the result starting with sixth place.

1265
01:05:00,413 --> 01:05:04,263
Please show the sixth-place series.

1266
01:05:04,263 --> 01:05:07,073
[Han Soo Ji's "Snakes and Ladders"]

1267
01:05:07,073 --> 01:05:10,043
[Park So Rang's "Is This Marriage Valid?"]

1268
01:05:10,043 --> 01:05:12,633
[Han Sang Il's "My Love Story
Only I Don't Know About"]

1269
01:05:12,633 --> 01:05:15,273
[Yang Gyeong Hee's "Joseon Man,
MZ Woman, and a Gay Man"]

1270
01:05:15,273 --> 01:05:19,143
[Lee Yoo Jin's "Cast Them If You See the Path"]

1271
01:05:19,143 --> 01:05:23,723
[Lee Joo Seung's "The Murderer Upstairs"]

1272
01:05:24,273 --> 01:05:25,903
[Who will be in 6th place in the final round?]

1273
01:05:26,493 --> 01:05:29,073
I just want to be in fifth place.

1274
01:05:29,073 --> 01:05:30,773
I want to fall in the middle.

1275
01:05:34,493 --> 01:05:36,733
[Yang Gyeong Hee's "Joseon Man,
MZ Woman, and a Gay Man"]

1276
01:05:36,733 --> 01:05:39,723
Director Yang Gyeong Hee.

1277
01:05:39,723 --> 01:05:43,833
"Joseon Man, MZ Woman,
and a Gay Man" is in sixth place.

1278
01:05:43,833 --> 01:05:49,593
With 31 stops and an average
viewing time of 176.87 seconds,

1279
01:05:49,593 --> 01:05:53,413
you're in sixth place. Thank you so much.

1280
01:05:53,413 --> 01:05:56,233
[Heartfelt applause for Director Yang Gyeong Hee]

1281
01:05:56,233 --> 01:05:58,653
We'll move right along.

1282
01:05:58,653 --> 01:06:01,903
- Please reveal the fifth-place director.
- Moving right along.

1283
01:06:01,903 --> 01:06:04,273
[Everyone is nervous]

1284
01:06:04,273 --> 01:06:05,483
[Park So Rang's "Is This Marriage Valid?"]

1285
01:06:05,483 --> 01:06:09,743
Fifth place goes to Park So Rang's
"Is This Marriage Valid?"

1286
01:06:09,743 --> 01:06:11,653
With 32 stops,

1287
01:06:11,653 --> 01:06:15,093
and the average viewing time of 202.72 seconds,

1288
01:06:15,093 --> 01:06:18,043
you're in fifth place. Thank you very much.

1289
01:06:18,043 --> 01:06:21,403
There is quite a gap between the two.

1290
01:06:22,203 --> 01:06:25,673
Please reveal the fourth-place director.

1291
01:06:25,673 --> 01:06:29,513
[Who will take 4th place?]

1292
01:06:29,513 --> 01:06:31,283
Who could it be?

1293
01:06:31,283 --> 01:06:32,853
The fourth place goes to...

1294
01:06:33,703 --> 01:06:35,713
The fourth place goes to...

1295
01:06:35,713 --> 01:06:39,043
Director Han Sang Il's "My Love Story
Only I Don't Know About."

1296
01:06:39,043 --> 01:06:40,683
With 28 stops,

1297
01:06:40,683 --> 01:06:44,693
and the average viewing time of
205.36 seconds, you're in fourth place.

1298
01:06:44,693 --> 01:06:48,513
Even though the stop count was higher,

1299
01:06:48,513 --> 01:06:53,033
this means they mostly voted toward the end.

1300
01:06:53,033 --> 01:06:54,233
That's right.

1301
01:06:54,233 --> 01:06:56,573
[6th place: Yang Gyeong Hee /
5th place: Park So Rang]

1302
01:06:56,573 --> 01:06:57,973
[4th place: Han Sang Il]

1303
01:06:59,303 --> 01:07:04,773
I just wanted to be in the middle,
but I saw the number six.

1304
01:07:04,773 --> 01:07:06,583
It was a bit rough.

1305
01:07:07,323 --> 01:07:08,413
I'm satisfied.

1306
01:07:08,413 --> 01:07:11,393
I made it out of the fire alive.

1307
01:07:11,393 --> 01:07:15,653
I haven't had big results in my career.

1308
01:07:15,653 --> 01:07:18,823
But that process wasn't a waste.

1309
01:07:18,823 --> 01:07:22,403
I was happy to prove that to myself.

1310
01:07:23,323 --> 01:07:25,273
There are three directors left.

1311
01:07:25,273 --> 01:07:28,153
Directors Han Soo Ji, Lee Yoo Jin,
and Lee Joo Seung.

1312
01:07:28,153 --> 01:07:30,153
I'll announce the final three.

1313
01:07:30,153 --> 01:07:33,743
Who is the third-place director?

1314
01:07:33,743 --> 01:07:35,953
Please reveal.

1315
01:07:35,953 --> 01:07:38,533
[Extremely nervous]

1316
01:07:43,523 --> 01:07:48,383
The third place goes to Director Han Soo Ji.

1317
01:07:48,383 --> 01:07:50,293
Congratulations.

1318
01:07:50,293 --> 01:07:54,313
It's a bit disappointing that I'm in third place.

1319
01:07:54,313 --> 01:07:57,243
But I'm grateful that I made it this far.

1320
01:07:57,243 --> 01:08:00,243
I tried out a new genre.

1321
01:08:00,243 --> 01:08:03,823
That was very meaningful to me.

1322
01:08:03,823 --> 01:08:06,623
I am so grateful to everyone who joined me.

1323
01:08:06,623 --> 01:08:09,883
My crew worked hard as
if it were their project. Thank you.

1324
01:08:09,883 --> 01:08:11,763
Thank you.

1325
01:08:11,763 --> 01:08:14,043
Congratulations. Congratulations.

1326
01:08:14,043 --> 01:08:15,633
Director Han Soo Ji.

1327
01:08:15,633 --> 01:08:19,373
The first short drama competition
show in Korea, Director's Arena.

1328
01:08:19,373 --> 01:08:22,793
We're only awaiting the
announcement of the winner.

1329
01:08:22,793 --> 01:08:24,503
This is so daebak.

1330
01:08:25,623 --> 01:08:28,013
[Their legs turn into jelly]

1331
01:08:28,013 --> 01:08:30,333
- Fighting!
- Are you okay?

1332
01:08:30,333 --> 01:08:32,713
- Are you okay?
- My legs turned weak.

1333
01:08:32,713 --> 01:08:34,253
It's okay.

1334
01:08:34,253 --> 01:08:35,453
Will you stay like that?

1335
01:08:35,453 --> 01:08:37,353
To be in the same frame, should I join you?

1336
01:08:37,353 --> 01:08:38,633
[So funny]

1337
01:08:38,633 --> 01:08:41,113
We're awaiting the announcement of the winner.

1338
01:08:41,113 --> 01:08:45,493
Which director will win
100 million won and the title

1339
01:08:45,493 --> 01:08:47,793
of the first winner ever?

1340
01:08:47,793 --> 01:08:51,353
The one person I'm about to name...

1341
01:08:51,353 --> 01:08:55,063
is the winner of Director's Arena.

1342
01:08:55,063 --> 01:08:57,653
Will it be Lee Yoo Jin?

1343
01:08:57,653 --> 01:09:00,413
Or will it be Lee Joo Seung?

1344
01:09:00,413 --> 01:09:02,943
You both have a full head of hair.

1345
01:09:04,493 --> 01:09:08,133
I am learning a lot from this show.

1346
01:09:08,133 --> 01:09:10,663
We're awaiting the final announcement.

1347
01:09:10,663 --> 01:09:14,403
Is there something you want
to share in this moment?

1348
01:09:14,403 --> 01:09:16,493
Are you okay? You're hyperventilating. I'm scared.

1349
01:09:16,493 --> 01:09:19,793
I am so happy, and it feels like
a dream that I came this far.

1350
01:09:19,793 --> 01:09:21,333
Let me...

1351
01:09:21,333 --> 01:09:23,313
I wasn't dreaming. I'm alive.

1352
01:09:23,313 --> 01:09:27,243
- Thank you.
- Joo Seung, this was hidden camera.

1353
01:09:27,243 --> 01:09:29,673
Geez!

1354
01:09:29,673 --> 01:09:31,773
Lee Kyung Kyu, please come out.

1355
01:09:31,773 --> 01:09:34,273
[His kind of a joke]

1356
01:09:34,273 --> 01:09:38,453
This is like a dream. It's impressive.

1357
01:09:38,453 --> 01:09:41,563
I'll announce the final winner.

1358
01:09:41,563 --> 01:09:44,643
[Drum roll]

1359
01:09:46,003 --> 01:09:48,583
The final winner is...

1360
01:09:50,413 --> 01:09:52,633
Cha Tae Hyun, please make the announcement.

1361
01:09:53,393 --> 01:09:59,453
Director Arena's final winning director is...

1362
01:10:00,693 --> 01:10:04,323
[Who will it be?]

1363
01:10:06,053 --> 01:10:08,223
Lee...

1364
01:10:08,223 --> 01:10:10,133
[Who will win 100 million won?]

1365
01:10:10,133 --> 01:10:12,733
[He was in danger of elimination in Round 1]

1366
01:10:12,733 --> 01:10:14,873
[He defeated a potential winner,
Director Han Soo Ji]

1367
01:10:14,873 --> 01:10:17,693
[Dark horse, Director Lee Joo Seung?]

1368
01:10:18,083 --> 01:10:20,363
[Starting out Round 1 with no stops]

1369
01:10:20,363 --> 01:10:22,593
[He was in first place until Round 2]

1370
01:10:23,033 --> 01:10:25,153
[Director Lee Yoo Jin with a streak of wins?]

1371
01:10:27,833 --> 01:10:29,153
Lee...

1372
01:10:32,933 --> 01:10:34,313
Lee...

1373
01:10:36,203 --> 01:10:37,653
Joo Seung!

1374
01:10:37,653 --> 01:10:40,273
[Director Lee Joo Seung]

1375
01:10:40,273 --> 01:10:41,233
Joo Seung!

1376
01:10:41,233 --> 01:10:44,833
[Daebak]

1377
01:10:45,393 --> 01:10:47,223
[Covering his mouth]

1378
01:10:47,223 --> 01:10:50,183
Director Lee Joo Seung received seven stops

1379
01:10:50,183 --> 01:10:53,803
and had an average viewing time
of 248.89 seconds.

1380
01:10:53,803 --> 01:10:57,203
You came in first place and are the final winner.

1381
01:10:59,883 --> 01:11:02,493
You are the final winner, Director Lee Joo Seung.

1382
01:11:02,493 --> 01:11:06,913
To be honest, I had no idea.

1383
01:11:06,913 --> 01:11:11,763
I think it's because I had
talented people around me.

1384
01:11:11,763 --> 01:11:14,663
I'll share this joy with them. Thank you.

1385
01:11:14,663 --> 01:11:15,933
[Congrats]

1386
01:11:15,933 --> 01:11:21,363
I came in second place,

1387
01:11:21,363 --> 01:11:23,943
but this is a win to me.

1388
01:11:23,943 --> 01:11:26,363
This was a long and hard journey,

1389
01:11:26,363 --> 01:11:31,963
but I was motivated to work harder as a director.

1390
01:11:31,963 --> 01:11:34,233
I want to thank the judges.

1391
01:11:34,233 --> 01:11:38,443
I sincerely thank each one of you.

1392
01:11:41,243 --> 01:11:43,133
[Directing Award: Canon film camera]

1393
01:11:43,133 --> 01:11:44,693
[50 million won]

1394
01:11:44,693 --> 01:11:46,313
[100 million won]

1395
01:11:46,313 --> 01:11:49,493
To me, Director's Arena was...

1396
01:11:50,703 --> 01:11:52,693
a fresh starting point.

1397
01:11:52,693 --> 01:11:55,063
Opportunity comes to those who are prepared.

1398
01:11:55,063 --> 01:11:56,933
A rare chance that came to me.

1399
01:11:56,933 --> 01:11:58,693
I gained great colleagues,

1400
01:11:58,693 --> 01:12:02,823
and I learned a lot from them on this show.

1401
01:12:02,823 --> 01:12:09,413
It brought back some passion and dream for me.

1402
01:12:10,683 --> 01:12:12,653
A turning point.

1403
01:12:12,653 --> 01:12:18,153
I got to show everyone the moments of

1404
01:12:18,153 --> 01:12:22,493
fulfilling a dream of a lifetime.
I'm grateful for it.

1405
01:12:22,493 --> 01:12:25,023
It's over. It's like my ex-lover.

1406
01:12:25,023 --> 01:12:26,593
I had a great time.

1407
01:12:26,593 --> 01:12:28,673
It's a part of my past that
I don't look back on and regret.

1408
01:12:28,673 --> 01:12:31,233
I'll forever remember the Arena.

1409
01:12:31,233 --> 01:12:32,733
The Arena.

1410
01:12:32,733 --> 01:12:34,643
Director's Arena.

1411
01:12:35,903 --> 01:12:37,633
[We look forward to the directors' next stories]

1412
01:12:37,633 --> 01:12:39,243
[We cheer you on]

1413
01:12:39,243 --> 01:12:43,013
It was an honor to make a special appearance.

1414
01:12:43,013 --> 01:12:46,513
"Cast Them If You See the Path," fighting.

1415
01:12:46,513 --> 01:12:49,013
Director Lee Yoo Jin, you're the best.

1416
01:12:52,233 --> 01:12:55,303
"Snakes and Ladders," fighting!

1417
01:12:55,303 --> 01:12:58,263
"The Beggar Couple Joins the Chaebol Family."

1418
01:12:58,263 --> 01:13:01,293
- Fighting!
- Fighting!

1419
01:13:36,343 --> 01:13:41,483
[Please cheer for their next stories]
